title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread dinner rolls flat on a pan and bake.
Let cool.
Let cream cheese soften so that mixing of cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise will be easier.
Spread over cooled crust and slice in small squares.
Sprinkle the veggies and serve cool.

title: herb and orange grilled chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix together garlic, orange peel, salt, thyme, rosemary and pepper.
Slip fingers between the skin and flesh of the chicken, leaving the skin attached.
Spread 1/4 of herb mixture under the skin of each chicken quarter, pulling the skin back over spices.
Mix together orange juice, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce.
Place chicken on prepared grill, skin-side up, about 8 inches from heat.
Cook, turning and basting with orange juice mixture every 5 minutes, for about 40 minutes, or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.

title: mint apple crisp
directions: Beat well together the first three ingredients.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon, then mix well.
Add apples, mint and nuts; fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: merry sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Gradually beat in flour mixture (batter will be stiff).
Stir in 1 cup chips.
Roll by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Gently press 3 to 4 of the remaining morsels on top of the cookies.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, or until cookies are puffed and slightly golden at edges.
Let stand on cookie sheets for 2 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheets; cool.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions.
In casserole dish, put layer of crackers, onions and 1/2 can of soup.
Put another layer of each. Top with crackers and cheese.
Mix together the eggs and milk. Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pecan pie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter in a small bowl. Beat on low speed until crumbly. Press into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan. Bake 15 minutes. Combine sugar, pumpkin, milk, eggs and pie spice in a large mixer bowl. Beat at medium speed 1 to 2 minutes. Pour over crust. Bake 20 minutes.

title: noel fruit bars
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in confectioners sugar.
Stir in melted butter.
Sift together dry ingredients; fold into egg mixture with nuts and fruits.
Spread in greased 9-inch by 9-inch by 2-inch baking pan.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into bars; frost with butter frosting and top with candied cherries, if desired.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen bar cookies.

title: baked spaghetti with sausage
directions: In large frying pan, crumble sausage. Brown over medium heat until no longer pink; drain. Prepare pasta according to package.

title: oyster pie
directions: Grease casserole well.
Put a layer of oysters, then a layer of cracker crumbs. Repeat these layers, sprinkling thyme through the oyster layers.
Dot butter through pie.
After several layers, pour milk over the entire pie until mixture is level with top of casserole.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 400°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball.
Refrigerate.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Finely chop ham and onion.
Place in a bowl.
Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard; stir to combine.

title: butterscotch pecan squares
directions: Melt
butter and blend with sugar.
Add slightly beaten egg. Let
mixture stand to cool.
Add sifted and measured dry ingredients.
Stir	in
pecans.
Spread
in
a greased pan 8 x 8-inches.
Bake
in
350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and let cool in pan.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add melted chocolate, coffee, and almond or rum extract. Stir in flour and 1 cup of pecans. Pour into pastry shell; sprinkle with remaining pecans. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until done. Cool; top with whipped cream if desired. Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Brown meat.
Add remaining ingredients in layers in order given.
Cover when steaming.
Turn to low and simmer for 30 minutes.
This can be made ahead.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and food coloring, if desired.
Pour into crust; bake 8 minutes.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Top with whipped topping.
Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Brown roast in hot oil and also in Dutch oven.
Drain off drippings.
Add water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat; simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until roast is done.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until it stands in a soft peak.
Gradually add brown sugar and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 250°.
Turn oven off and leave in oven 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Put in airtight container.
Freezes well.

title: asparagus roll-ups
directions: Slice off crust from bread.
Using a rolling pin, roll each slice of bread until it is very thin.
Spread a thin layer of mayonnaise on each slice and sprinkle pepper on the mayonnaise (a pepper mill works best).
Roll up one spear of asparagus in each piece of bread.
Serve chilled on a bed of Boston/romaine lettuce.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cut up into a 1-pint jar the olives, pimientos, green pepper and onions.
Then add lemon juice, vinegar, salt and salad oil. Let stand overnight and serve over a green or fresh vegetable salad.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Beat ingredients together until smooth and slightly thickened. Pour into single cooked pie shell.
Chill until thickened like pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: angel food cheesecake
directions: Mix jellos and hot water and cold water.
Let set.
After this is set, add cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and cream.
Mix jello and cream cheese mixture well, then pour into an 8 x 12-inch pan lined with slices of angel food cake.
Refrigerate until well set.

title: egg and sausage strata
directions: Line greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with bread cubes; set aside. In a skillet, brown sausage with onion and pepper; drain.
Stir in pimientos; sprinkle over bread.

title: marinated broccoli and mushrooms
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into bite sizes.
Place in plastic or stainless steel refrigerator container that has a tight cover. Wash or wipe off mushrooms; thinly slice them and place on top of broccoli.
In a separate bowl, combine vinegar, parsley, pepper, salt, lemon juice, oil and sugar.
Mash or chop garlic very fine and add to dressing.
Mix well and pour over vegetables.
Cover container tightly and refrigerate, turning container several times a day.
Drain well and serve.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook amount of potatoes desired in salted water.
When the potatoes are cooked, drain and cut the potatoes in small pieces. Add black pepper, chopped onion, oil and vinegar to your taste.

title: salad medley
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup syrup. Toss pineapple lightly with ham, grapes and cheese. Line salad bowl with your favorite lettuce or a mixture of lettuce leaves. Spoon salad mixture onto lettuce. Chill.

title: veal chops with lemon sauce
directions: Place chops on unheated broiler pan rack.
Broil chops 3 to 4 inches from heat for 5 minutes.
Turn chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Broil 5 minutes or until done.

title: turkey or chicken dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with broth.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Serve with sliced veggies and corn chips.

title: dorothy's cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onions and salt, then chill.
Shape into balls. Roll in remaining nuts.
Refrigerate until well chilled. Garnish with parsley.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Roll a biscuit into a 9-inch rope; bring ends together and seal.
Repeat with remaining biscuits.
Dip each circle in the melted butter or margarine, then in the cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Twist circles into a figure 8; place on greased baking sheet.
Sprinkle with nuts if desired. Bake at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 4 or 5 servings.

title: egg strata
directions: Mix butter and Dijon mustard and spread on bread.
Spread layer of bread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with layer of grated cheese and layer of cooked sausage.
Layer one more time. Pour milk and egg mixture over bread.
Cook at 350° until top is brown.

title: double lime punch
directions: In punch bowl, stir together all ingredients.
Serve in punch cups.
Yields 10 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: american apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Spray 9-inch deep-dish pie plate with vegetable spray. In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour, lemon peel, cinnamon and nutmeg; mix well. Add apples to sugar mixture; stir until coated. Stir in raisins; spoon into prepared pan. Place pie crust on top of filling. Trim edges, pressing against edge of pan. Using a sharp knife, cut 2 or 3 slits or steam vents in the crust.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flakes and melted margarine. Spread in lasagna pan.
Just before serving, top with crushed corn flakes and melted margarine.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: lisa's broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli by directions on package. Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake for about 30 to 40 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cover potatoes with water and bring to boil.
Reduce to medium heat and simmer until tender.
Drain and place in a mixing bowl; beat potatoes with mixer until fluffy.
Cut cream cheese into small pieces and beat in with the oleo.
Beat in sour cream and seasonings.
Scrape into buttered casserole dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature.
Reheat at 300°, uncovered, for about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: yeast corn bread
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Measure warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle or crumble yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, the beaten eggs, flour and cornmeal.
Beat until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Batter will be stiff.
Turn into 2 greased 8-inch round cake pans or 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Cover, let rise in warm place free from draft until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: fruit dip for apples
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Beat in vanilla and brown sugar.
Slice apples to dip.

title: white chili
directions: Drain water off beans.
In large pot, combine drained beans, broth, garlic, onions, soup and seasonings.
Simmer 3 hours.
Add more broth, if necessary.
Add pork, stirring only to combine. Garnish top of chili with cheese and green onions.

title: microwave crab dip
directions: Place butter in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 45 seconds.
Add onion, garlic and parsley.
Cover and microwave on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Add cream cheese and cover. Microwave on High 1 minute.
Stir in Worcestershire, Tabasco and salt; mix well.
Gently stir in crabmeat.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes, until thoroughly heated.
Serve with crackers.

title: diane's shrimp alfredo
directions: Saute butter and garlic, then add shrimp and mushrooms.
Saute for approximately 5 minutes, or until shrimp are pink.
Add half and half, Velveeta cheese, and pepper.
Saute for a minute or two, then add Parmesan cheese and saute approximately 10 minutes. Serve over angel hair pasta.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: tomato lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Lay flat on foil to cool.
Heat oil; add onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring to break up tomatoes; set aside.

title: fruit slush
directions: Separate oranges; cut into bite size pieces.
Combine all ingredients in a large container.
Place in freezer.
Leave for 2 hours or more and scrape sides.
Repeat until frozen.
Serve with ginger ale, 7-Up, Sprite or other favorite beverage.

title: minute fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla into saucepan.
Bring to a full boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir and cool for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat to spreading consistency.
Makes a hard frosting and keeps well.

title: lemon pineapple cheese salad
directions: Boil pineapple, water and sugar in saucepan.
Remove from heat and add lemon jello and blend.
Cool completely and add grated cheese and nuts, mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into mold.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: granny's chewy sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with 3 inch cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: cucumber apple ring
directions: Peel cucumbers; remove seeds and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Place slices in a crock or enamel canner.
Mix lime with 8 1/2 quarts of water.
Pour over slices in crock.
Let stand 24 hours.
Pour off lime water and rinse real good.
Soak slices in ice water for 3 hours.
Drain.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix jello with water and stir until dissolved.
Set aside. Mix pineapple, cottage cheese, shredded cheese, pecans and whipped topping until well blended.
Add jello mixture and stir well. Refrigerate until set.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, peppers, garlic and salt in large saucepan.
Stir in 1 tray of ice cubes and let stand 3 hours (drain).
Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard, celery seed and turmeric and boil 2 minutes.
Pour over pickles.
Bring to a boil and cool. Pack into freezer containers and freeze.

title: olive spread appetizer
directions: Mix. Microwave for 10 minutes, stirring 2 to 3 times. Spread on crackers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease sheets.
In a large bowl, combine mix, vanilla and egg.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto prepared baking sheets.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 24 cookies.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven-crusty fish
directions: Cut
fish
into serving pieces allowing about 1/4 pound for each
serving.
Combine
milk and salt.
Dip fish in milk, then in	crushed
cereal.
Arrange
on
greased or foil-lined shallow baking
pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until flaky.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Boil and mash potatoes. Take hamburger and mix with soup.
Put in a small baking dish. Spoon on mashed potatoes.
Slice margarine and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and vegetable.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pink dream
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar and cook 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: toffee cookies
directions: Place graham crackers on a vegetable-sprayed jelly roll pan in a single layer.
Boil margarine and sugar 3 minutes.
Pour evenly over crackers. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Watch closely so they don't burn.
Let cool a few minutes before loosening, then cool on a wire rack.
Store when cool in a covered container.

title: appetizer sausage rolls
directions: Roll out each biscuit on floured surface and cut into 4 strips.
Roll each sausage in a biscuit strip and moisten end of biscuit to make stick.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 450° until biscuits are brown.

title: pineapple pudding pie
directions: Mix together the pineapple, sour cream and pudding.
Add to crust.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs. Chill until pudding is solid.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together and chill several hours or overnight.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring brown sugar and margarine to a boil.
Add milk and boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add confectioners sugar using more if needed and vanilla.
Good with chocolate cupcakes.

title: first prize chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8-inch pans.
Melt butter and chocolate together over low heat.
Cool.
Blend eggs until foamy, about 2 minutes.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, soda and sugar.
Blend dry ingredients into buttermilk mixture, then stir in melted butter and chocolate. Pour batter into pans.
Bake about 20 minutes.
Frost with dark chocolate frosting.

title: traditional baked lasagna
directions: In a Dutch oven over medium heat, cook ground beef, onion, garlic and fennel seed until meat is browned.
Drain and return to pan.
Stir in pasta, sauce, basil, oregano and pepper; continue cooking until heated through.
Heat oven to 375°.
On bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, sprayed with non-stick cooking spray, spread 1 cup sauce.
Top with 1/3 lasagna noodles, sauce, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layering 2 more times. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Butter 8 x 11 1/2-inch dish.
Mix cake mix, egg and butter or margarine; press in bottom of dish.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and beaten eggs.
Pour on top of mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: skier's french toast
directions: Heat butter, brown sugar and corn syrup until sugar is dissolved. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Layer bread on top of syrup mixture. In a bowl, mix eggs, milk, vanilla and nutmeg. Pour over bread slices. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 2 minutes.
Stir in broth and tortellini.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Mix in 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer until tortellini are just tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, spinach and basil into soup.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Serve with extra Parmesan.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then chill for 2 hours.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Chop cabbage into medium size pieces and boil in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix butter, flour and milk until smooth.
Add cheese and cook until thick and cheese is melted. Layer cabbage and cheese sauce in a baking dish.
End with cheese sauce.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and cook for 3 minutes (No Longer). Add oatmeal and peanut butter. Mix well. Drop on buttered wax paper.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and cook to soft ball stage. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered 9 x 9-inch dish.
Let cool, then cut in 1-inch squares.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger.
Add onion, celery and green pepper.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let simmer until onions, celery and green peppers are tender.
I've found that 1 or 2 tablespoons of brown sugar improves the flavor.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: mom's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs until well done.
Cool eggs and potatoes, then peel and dice.
Peel and dice onion.
Mix in salad dressing, mustard and pickle relish.
Add salt, pepper and seasoning salt.

title: ham glaze
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add other ingredients.
Cook for a few minutes, until it is as thick as you want it.
Serve over ham.

title: diabetic apple muffins
directions: Cream shortening and Sugar Twin; add egg.
Mix well.
Mix or sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Add apple and milk to egg mixture along with flour.
Stir until well blended; do not overmix.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni tuna salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.
May add more relish and/or mayonnaise according to taste.

title: green salad with fruit
directions: Mix together and put dressing on at the last moment; mix well. Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in pie pan. Needs no pie crust.
It forms as it bakes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer on high for 2 minutes.
Eggs should be light and fluffy.
Add sugars and flour; beat on high 2 minutes.
Add melted butter and beat.
Mix in nuts and chocolate morsels.
Spoon mixture into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add the eggs, then the mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients; add water.
Bake in 2 (7 1/2 x 4-inch) pans or 1 regular loaf pan which have been greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: hamburg roll potato
directions: Saute the onion and garlic lightly in hot drippings.
Remove from heat and mix in the beef and egg.
Soften the bread in water to which salt, oregano and pepper have been added.
Mix well. Spread on a piece of waxed paper and sprinkle with the crumbs. Turn the beef mixture out on the crumbs and pat into a rectangle about 1/2-inch thick.
Beat the mashed potatoes with the parsley and spread over the meat.
Roll up the meat by lifting the wax paper along the long side of rectangle as you would a jelly roll. Lift the roll carefully into a shallow casserole dish, greased if meat is dry.
Place bacon strips on top.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven. Serve with mushroom soup or tomato sauce.

title: cider sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine all ingredients except Butter.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in Butter.
GOOD ON PANCAKES.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 2 tablespoons sugar together in a mixing bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine with two knives or a pastry blender until mixture looks like coarse cornmeal.
Pat an even layer of this crumbly pastry over bottom and halfway up sides of baking pan.
Use your hands and press firmly until it holds.
Skin fresh peaches and cut in half.
Drain canned peaches or thaw and drain frozen peaches.
Arrange peaches over bottom of pastry neatly and sprinkle with a mixture of remaining sugar and cinnamon.
Bake for 15 minutes, then pour a mixture of slightly beaten egg yolks and heavy or sour cream over the top. Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serve warm or cold.
Use 8-inch square pan.
May substitute apples.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour cherry and pineapple filling into cake dish.
Do not drain.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top and chip oleo up on top of filling.
Sprinkle nuts on top of it all.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: sheila's sticky buns(servings:  4)
directions: Preheat oven at 375°.
Coat sides and bottom of a tube pan with 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle bottom of pan with 3 tablespoons of the nuts.
Set aside.
In a small pan, melt the 1/2 cup of margarine; add brown sugar, water and nuts.
Heat to boiling, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Cut each biscuit in half and roll into a ball.
Place 20 balls in tube pan; sprinkle on some nuts and half of the sugar sauce.
Make a second layer, repeating the same process.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
When baked, invert pan immediately onto a large plate, allowing pan to remain over buns for a few moments to allow all the sauce to drip onto buns.
Remove pan.
Serve warm.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
In large bowl, beat butter, brown sugar and 3/4 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, soda and salt.
Add sugar mixture; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
In small bowl, combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon; sprinkle lightly over each cookie. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire cooling rack.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Put dates, Eagle Brand milk and nuts in double boiler and cook very thick.
Spread on Ritz crackers on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 or 6 minutes.
When cool, frost.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Melt baking soda in milk.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 8 minutes.

title: cheese caraway batter bread
directions: In a large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cheese, shortening, sugar, salt, caraway seed and 2 cups of the flour.
Blend for 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
(By hand, beat 300 vigorous strokes.) Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape batter from side of bowl. Cover; let rise in warm place until double, about 30 minutes.

title: toasty pecan pie
directions: Combine syrup, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix well. Add pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F (175°C).
In a medium mixing bowl, cream shortening, butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla until blended. Set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine dry ingredients, withholding the coconut until all other dry ingredients are blended.
Add coconut.
Combine wet and dry ingredients until moist.
Drop on greased cookie sheet about 1 to 2-inches apart. Bake for 10 minutes or until golden.
Remove from oven immediately, if overcooked cookies get HARD.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add pineapple (well drained), bananas and nuts. Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 X 13 dish and chill until firm.
Spread our cream evenly over set mixture.
Then pour remaining gelatin over and chill until firm.

title: white fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into glass baking dish.
Let cool and cut.

title: pam's chicken and cheese chowder
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in 2 cups boiling water.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes; do not drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and blend.
Add milk gradually; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add chicken and undrained vegetables.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serve with hot rolls or bread.

title: cinnamon raisin biscuits
directions: Mix flour,
1/2 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, oil and enough milk
to
make
dough.
Roll
or
pat
out	to 1/4-inch thickness. Spread
with melted oleo. Sprinkle with remaining 2 teaspoons cinnamon,
cup
sugar,
raisins
and nuts. Roll dough jelly roll
style.
Cut in about 1-inch slices.
Lay in oiled biscuit pan.
Bake	at
until
done.	Mix 1/2 cup powdered sugar and water and pour over biscuits as a glaze.

title: cherry pudding
directions: Cream together butter and 1 cup sugar.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture alternately.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Combine cherries with remaining sugar and juice; heat.
Pour over batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm from dish.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare 2 small packages instant vanilla pudding.
Mix according to directions on box, using 3 cups cold milk and one 8 ounce carton sour cream.
After pudding has thickened, fold in Cool Whip.
In large oblong pan or dish (13 x 9-inch), make layers of vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding mix.
Cover and refrigerate.
This pudding will not weep and will not turn dark.

title: miracle pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend for 15 seconds.
Pour into buttered pie pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: helen's dirty rice
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake at least 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 375°.

title: marble double chocolate cheesecake squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line an 8 or 9-inch square baking pan with foil, extending edges over side of pan.
In a small mixing bowl, beat butter, 1/2 cup sugar and salt until smooth. Stir together flour and cocoa.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until soft dough is formed.
Press dough onto bottom of prepared pan. Beat cream cheese and remaining 1/2 cup sugar until smooth. Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well.

title: football fan's taco pie
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in a pie or quiche pan.
Top with chili.
Mix green chilies and onions together; spread over chili. Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: pickles
directions: Put sliced pickles back in jar.
Add 2 or 3 pieces garlic and 3 cups sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Put back in refrigerator to chill.

title: orange bread
directions: Spread first 3 ingredients in a small bowl; set aside. Separate biscuits; gently separate individual biscuits in half. Place a cream cheese square between 2 halves, pinching sides to seal.
Dip in butter and dredge in reserved sugar mixture.
Stand biscuits on edge in a lightly greased 12-cup Bundt pan, spacing evenly.
Drizzle with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately invert onto serving plate.
Combine powdered sugar and orange juice; drizzle over warm bread.
Serve immediately.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil sweet potatoes with skins on.
Peel potatoes and place in a large mixing bowl.
Add margarine while hot.
Pour in all other ingredients; mix together at medium speed until blended well. Pour into ready pie shells.
Cook at 350° until firm and brown.

title: apple roll-overs
directions: Peel apples and slice.
Place 2 to 3 slices of apple onto crescent roll, then roll up and place in baking dish.
Melt sugar and butter in microwave and then stir in vanilla.
Pour over crescent rolls, then top with Mountain Dew.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cover with tinfoil after cooked.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together and put in baking pan.
Cover with ketchup. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Measure 1/4 of soup mix with meat, bread crumbs, onion, parsley and egg.
Shape into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Brown in skillet (in shortening) on all sides.
Blend remaining soup with water.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Serve over noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease bottom of 13 inch x 9 inch x 2 inch pan.
Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, pie spice and salt in large bowl.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Top with pecans.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake for 50 - 55 minutes until golden.
Cool completely. Serve with whipped topping.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 16 - 20.

title: macaroon kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolk, extract and orange juice; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in 3 cups coconut.
Cover tightly and chill 1 hour or until firm.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine 1 pkg. McCormick Brown Gravy Mix (0.87 oz.) with 1 1/2 pounds ground beef, 2 Tbsp. prepared horseradish, 1 Tbsp. parsley flakes, 1 tsp. basil leaves and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper. Shape into 1 in. meatballs.
Bake in preheated 375°F. oven 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with honey mustard.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix first seven ingredients. Pour 1/2 the batter into a greased 9x13 pyres dish sprayed with oil.
Sprinkle on cheese, layer meat next, sprinkle onion & pepper over the rest.
Pour remaining batter atop this. Bake 350 degree oven for 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook the potatoes and mash.
Combine with other ingredients. Pour in pastry shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Place beans in a bowl; add onion.
Mix oil and vinegar with sugar and salt.
Pour over beans; toss well.
Refrigerate, covered.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients into loaf pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick fudgies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo to a boil for 1 minute. Remove form heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until melted and add vanilla and quick oats.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, milk, cocoa and butter.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Spoon on wax paper or foil.

title: holiday cranberry slush(no alcohol)
directions: Put cranberry sauce in large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth. Add cranberry-apple concentrate, partially thawed lemonade and spices.
Mix until well blended and smooth.
Pour into large plastic container.
Add water and mix well.
Cover and freeze 2 hours.
Remove from freezer and stir again.
Freeze 8 hours or overnight.
To serve, thaw slush until it can be scooped easily. Mix about 1/2 cup slush with 7-Up or a lemon-lime soda in glass. Stir to blend.
Can be frozen and stored for several weeks.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix fruits in bowl.
Add pudding and mix well.
Fold in whipped topping.
Sprinkle pecans and coconut over the top.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes or until slightly tan color.
Cool.

title: squash a'la bama
directions: Clean, slice and boil squash until tender.
Drain squash and mix with other ingredients.
Bake in a buttered casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zippy shrimp with spaghetti
directions: Brown garlic lightly
in hot oil in saucepan. Add tomatoes with liquid, salt and basil.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Stir in tomato paste and oregano.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Stir in shrimp, garlic salt and horseradish.
Heat through.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Oven set at 350.
Bake 15 Minutes.
Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
(This is important!
Don't quit too soon!)
Add egg and continue stirring.
With flour in a separate bowl, mix with soda, baking powder, salt, cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add mashed persimmon pulp.
Add the flour blend.
Stir in the nuts and raisins.
Measure by tablespoons on a greased sheet and bake for fifteen minutes.
Place on a wire rack to cool so they will not steam against each other before putting into cookie jar.

title: santa fe pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, mix the cornmeal with 2/3 cup of cold water.
In a small heavy saucepan, bring the remaining 2/3 cup of water to a boil.
Gradually add the cornmeal mixture to the boiling water.
Lower heat and whisk with a fork until thick, about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.

title: french chocolate pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar in mixer.
Stir in cooled chocolate. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 5 minutes after each addition at high speed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into prepared pie shell. Chill.

title: tetrazzini
directions: *Can use ham, turkey, chicken or shrimp. Great recipe for leftover meat.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, pepper and salt. Mix well.

Dip chicken in vegetable oil; roll each piece in bread crumb mixture. Place chicken in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with more bread crumb mixture, if desired. Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until golden brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: caramel - topped oatmeal
directions: Combine oats and water in glass mixing bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, 3 to 4 minutes or until mixture boils, stirring once; set aside.

title: peanut ice cream dessert
directions: Press the wafer mixture into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spoon over 1/2 gallon softened ice cream.
Mix powdered sugar, chocolate chips, oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 10 minutes. Cool.
Pour mixture over ice cream.
Top with 1 pound salted Spanish peanuts.
Freeze.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9-inch pan.
Mix fresh fruit with 1/2 cup sugar. Mix 1 cup sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop flour mixture on melted oleo.
Cover with the fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: veggie squares
directions: Use 2 cookie sheets; press one can of rolls on each cookie sheet.
Bake according to directions on can.
Cool.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and mix lightly. Combine egg, shortening and applesauce.
Add to dry ingredients. Mix until dry ingredients are dampened.
Turn into a greased and floured 9 1/2 x 5 1/4 x 2 3/4-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: easy chicken pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions; drain.
Put in fridge to cool.
Cut up cooked chicken, peppers, onion and celery and mix with pasta.
Add Miracle Whip to desired taste.
(I add black olives and eggs sometimes.)
Top with salad toppings.
Chill; mix. Serve.

title: regal tuna casserole
directions: Drain and flake tuna.
Cook onion in margarine until tender (not brown).
Add peas, soup, mushrooms (undrained), catsup, mustard and salt.
Heat until hot and bubbling.
Fold in tuna, cheese, pimento and lemon.
Spoon tuna mixture into a shallow 2 quart baking dish, cover with foil, crimp; it securely to edge of dish.
Bake 15 minutes, uncover.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread, milk and raisins in bowl.
Let stand 15 minutes. In another bowl, beat eggs, sugar, oleo, vanilla and cinnamon. Pour into bread mixture and mix well.
Grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour in mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Cool.

title: vermicelli salad
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions; drain. Toss cooked vermicelli in corn oil to prevent sticking. Add all other ingredients. Mix well, then chill before serving.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels in milk in a double boiler until smooth. Remove from heat and add pecans. Mix well. Drop by teaspoons on greased waxed paper. Refrigerate. Melt chocolate morsels with paraffin in double boiler. Dip caramel balls in chocolate and drain on greased waxed paper.

title: chocolate cherry cheese cake
directions: Reserve 1 cup cake mix.
Combine rest of cake mix with oil and 1 egg.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan, lining the bottom and sides to form a crust.
Cream together reserved cake mix, 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add 3 eggs and vanilla and beat 1 minute.
Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes until firm.
Cool and refrigerate.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: chili con carne
directions: In saucepan, fry beef, garlic and onion until brown.
Add all other ingredients and cook at low temperature about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve with Italian bread or rolls.

title: cranberry-orange oatmeal bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar into medium-sized mixing bowl.
Stir in oats, grated orange peel and chopped cranberries.
Add oil, egg, orange juice and milk.
Stir only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool on wire rack about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool thoroughly.
Wrap cooled bread and store one day before slicing.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in a greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: self-crust chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place sliced eggs on chicken; add soup and chicken broth. Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Do not stir! Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix all together and serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers for up to 2 days.

title: nutrasweet chocolate pie
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 of the graham crackers.
Mix instant vanilla pudding with 2 1/2 cups skim milk; set aside.
Let this get thick.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip to pudding mix.
Start layering this, ending with the rest of the Cool Whip.

title: homemade chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla and whipping cream.
Mix well. Pour into freezer can.
Add Eagle Brand and chocolate syrup.
Stir well.
Add milk to fill line of freezer and freeze.

title: john morton's bourbon balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Shape into small balls and roll in additional powdered sugar. Chill. Store in tightly covered container in refrigerator.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Make syrup by combining 1/4 cup brown sugar, 2 tablespoons orange juice and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Set aside.

title: pink delight
directions: Cream Cool Whip with cherry pie filling.
Will be enough for 2 pie crusts or may be used without pie crusts.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.

title: fried chicken
directions: Oven-fried!
Combine flour, paprika, soup powder, dressing mix powder and seasoned salt.
Rinse fryer in water; drain.
Place flour mixture in plastic food bag.
Coat 1 piece chicken at a time in this.
Make single layer, skin side up, in greased baking pan. Drizzle each piece with bottled liquid margarine (about 2 tablespoons each piece).
Do not turn pieces.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, or until golden brown, basting 3 or 4 times in more margarine.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat all ingredients, except sour cream, with mixer until well blended.
By hand, fold in the sour cream.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid; set aside.
In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot oil, cook celery and garlic until tender, stirring constantly.
Add bouillon, tomatoes with their liquid, water, reserved clam juice, V-8 juice, parsley and pepper; heat to boiling.
Simmer 20 minutes and strain tomatoes out and discard. Add scallops, shrimp and clams.
Cook until shrimp are pink and opaque.
Serve with garlic bread.
Serves 4.

title: italian popcorn
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients.
Stir well and pour over popped corn, stirring to coat all pieces well.
Serve hot or cold.

title: grandma apel's cranberry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar and shortening together.
Then add orange juice and eggs.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Pour in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gooey butter cake(junk cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, egg and margarine together and press into bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar together.
Add vanilla. Pour over dough.
Bake 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a
large
bowl, cream margarine and sugars.
Beat in egg; add
vanilla
and
water.
Combine
flour, soda and salt. Stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts and semi-sweet chocolate chips; mix
well.
Drop
by
well rounded 1/2 teaspoonful onto greased cookie
sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool on wire racks. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Combine pudding mix and biscuit mix in a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add egg and milk.
Blend well. Stir in chips. Drop dough from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until light brown.
Remove from baking sheets and cool on racks. Store in covered containers. Makes 2 dozen.

title: butterscotch squares(idea recipe from pillsbury)
directions: Melt-in-your mouth Butterscotch Squares will fast become a family favorite for afternoon snacks or lunchbox treats.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Layer with cheese in casserole dish. Cook 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Freezes good.

title: pumpkin mousse pie
directions: Prepare pie filling as directed on package with 3/4 cup milk. Blend in pumpkin, spice, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spoon in pie shell. Chill for at least 4 hours.
Put remaining topping on pie.

title: best ice cream
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and milk.
Add fruit of your choice.
Peaches or strawberries are better.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.
Takes about 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix first 6 ingredients together and spread in casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of hot water.
Set in freezer to cool. Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Blend cream, sugar and jello together. Then in separate bowl, whip Milnot until stiff.
Add vanilla and blend with Milnot.
Add strawberries to cheese mixture.
Then blend slowly to cheese mixture the whipped cream.
Then pour into pan with graham crackers.
Sprinkle crushed graham crackers on top.
Refrigerate to cool.

title: "dirt"
directions: Crush cookies into crumbs; save 1/2 of them for topping.
Mix softened cream cheese and powdered sugar; blend well.
Set aside. Melt margarine and mix with 1/2 crushed cookie crumbs and put in bottom of flower pot.
Now take the cheese mixture and fold into it 8 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread over crumbs.
Mix pudding with milk and place on top of cream cheese mixture.
Insert a few gummy worms; set aside to cool or set.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and cover with cookie crumbs.
Chill at least 8 hours.

title: quick coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a bowl.
Mix in soft fat with fork until well blended.
Mix egg with milk and stir into flour mixture until well blended.
Fill greased pan half full and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, until cake springs back when touched.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Simmer celery and onion in water until tender, crumble toast and cornbread; mix in large bowl.
Add celery, onion and liquid in which they were cooked.
Add hot turkey broth to make a soft, moist mixture.
If more liquid is needed, add milk or cream of mushroom soup, diluted.
Add margarine and pour into a greased 4-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tuna puff
directions: Combine soup and cheese in a large saucepan; heat slowly, stirring constantly until cheese melts completely.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice, tuna, onion and pepper.
Beat egg yolks; slowly stir into tuna mixture.
Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into tuna mixture until no streaks of white remain.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until puffed and golden and firm in center.

title: bavarian apple torte
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients, mixing with pastry blender until crumbly like pie crust.
Press into bottom and 1-inch up sides of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook grits according to package.
Add butter, eggs and milk. Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and cook another 15 minutes.

title: mexican barbecue steak
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak in blender until well processed.
Pour over steak in Ziploc bag and marinate overnight, turning bag over 2 to
3 times in 24 hour period.
Preheat broiler or barbecue grill. Remove steak from marinade and grill or broil until desired doneness.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, stir meat until browned.
Drain off grease. Blend in soup, flour and tomato paste.
Stir in water.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13 inch greased pan, according to directions on box.
Let cool.
Meanwhile, beat Cool Whip with brown sugar.
Cut the cake in half horizontally to make two 9 x 13 layers.
On the first layer, spread a layer of caramel syrup, chopped nuts, and Cool Whip.
Place the other half of cake on top and spread Cool Whip on the cake.
Finish with a few chopped nuts.

title: drumsticks pierre
directions: Dust drumstick with seasoned flour.
Melt butter in large, heavy frying pan, with tight fitting cover.
Brown chicken over medium heat on all sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Add contents of can to cheese cubes in a small saucepan on low heat.
Heat until cheese melts; cool 10 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or fresh vegetables.

title: chocolate chip cookies at their best
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat first 4 ingredients on high until very light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each one.
Beat in vanilla extract and lemon juice.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and oats.
Gradually add to butter mixture, blending thoroughly.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop 1/4 cup (scant) of dough each onto lightly greased cookie sheets (about 3-inches apart).
Bake at 325° for 17 to 19 minutes.
Store in an airtight container.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: easy one pot meal
directions: Brown turkey, onion and celery in margarine.
Add balance of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 45 to 60 minutes for approximately 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice or chow mein noodles. Serves 4.

title: elvis presley pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add cream and vanilla. Blend well.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: creamy fudge candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage.
Take off stove and stir in chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts and Marshmallow Creme.	Stir well until dissolved.
Soften Marshmallow Creme by setting in warm water while cooking other ingredients. Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients put in 9x13 pan and top with corn flakes. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: cousin barbie's potatoes
directions: Add first 4 ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch or 10 x 14-inch baking pan.
Add melted butter to cornflake crumbs and sprinkle on mixture. Refrigerate overnight for added taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.

Drain fat from meat. Grate cheese. Add all ingredients (except 1/4 of cheese and tortilla chips). Heat on low heat. Line casserole dish with tortilla chips. Pour beef mixture over. Cover with remaining chips and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Broiler temperature 550°.
Broil for 4 minutes, turn and broil for 3 minutes, making about 6 servings.
In bowl, combine butter, oil, parsley, garlic, lemon juice,	salt
and
pepper. Place shrimp on two large broiler pans in
single
layer.
Pour on sauce.
Broil four inches from heat, for four minutes.
Turn shrimp over and broil for 3 minutes more or
until done.
Serve as an appetizer or with hot rice for main dish.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to reserved juice to measure 1/2 cup.
Combine with eggs, sugar, salt and lemon juice in saucepan; mix well.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add pineapple, celery, apples and pecans; mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon into an 8-inch square glass dish.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 20 to 30 minutes before serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Crush two candy bars and sprinkle over top.

title: club salad
directions: Make lime jello as directed on package.
Pour into long 9 x 13-inch dish and let chill until firm.
Then dissolve the lemon jello with 1 cup hot water only.
When cool but not jelled, add to the cream cheese and sugar, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well, then pour over first layer of lime jello.
Let that set.
Then mix strawberry jello as directed on package and let cool but not jelled.
Then pour over cream layer.

title: chicken (or turkey) fruit salad
directions: Combine and toss lightly with mayonnaise.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Place cracker in plastic bag and crush into fine crumbs, 1 1/4 cups.
Stir in sugar and melted butter.
Press into pie pan.

title: magic chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Add Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk.
Stir over rapidly boiling water for 5 to 10 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add water, salt and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.
Chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients together. Combine into zucchini mix ingredients.
Blend in raisins and/or nuts.
(Should yield enough for 2 loaves.)
Divide mixture into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Wrap in aluminum foil, store in refrigerator. (Also can be cooked in small individual loaf pans.)

title: snow peak frosting
directions: Place syrup in small pan and heat to a boil.
Add other ingredients and beat until stiff.

title: chicken broccoli strata(one dish meal)
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread.
Cut in chicken and broccoli and set aside.
Cut remaining bread in 1-inch cubes.
Place half of unbuttered cubes in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine chicken, vegetables, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasoning. Spoon over bread cubes.
Sprinkle remaining unbuttered cubes over chicken.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over all.
Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Spoon soup over top.
Sprinkle with buttered cubes.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top for last few minutes of baking.

title: canned pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Peel and put in a large kettle. Cover beets with vinegar, water, sugar and cloves.
Let come to a boil.
Fill jars with beets, then fill jars with syrup and seal. Beets keep for a long time.

title: bran muffins with raisins
directions: Mix cereal, milk, egg whites, cooking oil and applesauce in large bowl.
Let soak for 3 minutes until cereal is soft.
Add flour, sugar, salt (optional) and baking powder.
Mix well.
Batter will be thick.

title: fried rice(a wonderful side dish to the hawaiian chicken!)
directions: Fry chopped scallions in oil.
(When soft and light brown, rain and remove; set aside.)
In same oil, stir in egg and mix until a scrambled egg is formed.
(Note:
Oil will be hot from the fried scallions, therefore, eggs will cook quickly.)

title: chicken puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl mix together the cream cheese and 3 tablespoons melted butter.
Add the chicken, milk, pepper, minced onion and pimientos; mix well.
Separate each package of crescent rolls into 4 rectangles.
Divide the chicken filling evenly and spoon into center of each rectangle.
Bring ends up together and pinch closed.
Brush with remaining 2 tablespoons of melted butter.
Place puffs on a greased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix last three ingredients together. Pour into crust. Refrigerate until firm.

title: ham and cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 donut shapes from bread and set aside (or if in a hurry, cut bread in triangles).
Arrange a layer of bread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cheese and ham and top with bread.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over the ham and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Bake, uncovered at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: apple puffed pancake
directions: In a large bowl, mix eggs, milk, flour, sugar, vanilla, salt and cinnamon until well blended.
Batter will be slightly lumpy. Melt butter in a 12-inch porcelain quiche dish or 13 x 9-inch baking dish in oven.
Add apple slices to baking dish.
Return to oven until butter sizzles.
Do not brown.
Remove dish from oven and immediately pour batter over apples.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in middle of 425° oven 20 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: spaghetti marco polo
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Make as much spaghetti as you wish and add all other ingredients to taste.

title: spaghetti
directions: Get a slice of bread.
Put peanut butter on, then jelly.
Put another piece of bread.
Eat it.

title: dump salad
directions: Do not dissolve jello.
Add dry to the pineapple and stir; blend in cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill mixture 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger,
pork	sausage
and add onion and bell pepper.
Drain.
Add
soup, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer until done.
Remove from heat and add cheese.
Roll mixture in 12 to	15 corn tortillas, place in casserole and add remaining mix on top.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.	Bake at 350° for 34 to 45 minutes.

title: thunderbolt kraut chocolate cake
directions: Whip cream with remaining ingredients until peaks form. Spread on cake.

title: italian lovers snack
directions: Lightly butter bread.
Cut into 3-inch squares.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned.
In a saucepan, heat tomato sauce and add Parmesan cheese to taste.
Dip your bread squares in the sauce.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour.
Add milk, cream and broth.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens and comes to a boil. Reduce heat.
Stir in chicken and dash of pepper.
Heat again just to boiling.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: jackie's fruit cocktail cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add dry ingredients.
Add coconut, pecans and fruit.
Bake in slightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Will also need 10 pt. jars.

title: canned apple pie filling
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then gradually add sugar.
Cook mixture until smooth and bubbly.
Add salt, lemon juice and food coloring.
Fix 6 to 7 pounds apples, peeled, cored and sliced. Pack into hot jars.
Pour syrup over apples.
Use knife to circulate to bottom of jar.
Process in water bath for 20 minutes.

title: wava's meat loaf recipe
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put in a loaf pan and cover with 2 strips bacon that have been cut in small pieces.
(If you like bacon flavor.)
Pour 8 ounce can of tomato sauce over meat loaf. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: grated sweet potatoes
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry dessert (pretzel)
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese and sugar, then set aside.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour over cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate until firm.
A dab of Cool Whip on top is nice when serving.

title: fudge
directions: Butter 9-inch cake pan. Set aside. Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in heavy 4-quart saucepan. Stir in milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to full rolling boil. Boil, without stirring, to hard-ball stage or 234° on candy thermometer or use cold water and drop a few drops of candy until it makes a ball. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Cool until butter melts, then beat until candy loses some of its gloss and thickens. Pour into pan.

title: sugar coated pecan
directions: Boil sugar, milk and cinnamon to soft ball stage.
Add in 1 big tablespoon butter.
Stir in pecan halves.
Stir until well-coated.
Turn out on waxed paper and separate.

title: blushing apples
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Core the apples and peel halfway down. Place apples in a baking dish, with the peeled side up.
Melt the butter, then stir in the flour, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Spoon the mixture onto the tops and into the centers of the apples. Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 10 minutes until crusty, then lower the heat to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes until tender.

title: apple relish
directions: Do not use food chopper.
Combine all ingredients, except spice.
Put spices in small bag (cloth).
Boil slowly until mixture is thick.
Seal in hot sterile jars.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Divide whipped topping among 6 dessert glasses, using about 1/3 cup in each.

With the back of a spoon, make a depression in the center and spread topping up the sides of the glasses. Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package for pudding. Spoon pudding mixture into glasses; chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. From oranges, grate 1 tablespoon peel and squeeze 3/4 cup juice; set aside.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In medium bowl, beat oil, egg and orange juice until blended; stir into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Gently stir in cranberries, walnuts and orange peel. Spoon batter evenly into loaf pan.
Bake 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center of bread comes out clean.
Cool bread in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
With sharp knife, loosen bread from sides of pan, then remove bread.
Cool bread completely on wire rack.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and margarine until well mixed.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Add powdered sugar; mix well.
Make into melon ball size balls and put in refrigerator until cold.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain all fruits.
Mix together and chill.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Rub oil onto potatoes before baking.
Bake.
Let cool.
Cut in halves.
Scrape out potato and mash.
Save skins.
Add dip and bacon to mashed potatoes.
Place in potato skins.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop
by tablespoons and deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Drain pickles and slice lengthwise.
Place back in jar.
Add sugar, celery seed and onion.
Pour vinegar over pickles.
Seal. Keep turning jar until sugar is dissolved.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Combine peaches.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cook at 400° about 40 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: bacon "stuffing wraps"
directions: Mix Stove Top as instructed on box.
Wrap bacon (separate pieces of bacon).
Place toothpicks in center (to hold in place). Place under broiler until bacon is cooked.
Serve hot.

title: jasper's barbecue sauce recipe
directions: Mix brown sugar and dry mustard (dry mustard has a tendency to clump) together. If using onion powder and garlic powder, add it to the brown sugar. Saut the onion and garlic using Pam. Mix in the rest of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour or more.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
well. Grease and flour a tube cake pan well.
Put wax paper in the bottom of the pan. Bake about 2 hours at 275° to 300°.

title: roasted tomato sauce with pasta
directions: Roast in oven on foil covered pan all tomatoes for 1 hour at 350°.
Remove and let cool.
When cooled, peel skin and remove core; throw core and skin away.
Be sure to keep all juice and meat from the tomato.
Cut into small pieces.
In large skillet, brown garlic in olive oil.
When garlic is lightly browned, add tomatoes and juice.
While stirring, add parsley, oregano, salt and pepper; mix well.
Let simmer.

title: fruit bars
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy. Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well forming crumbs. Press half of crumb mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Spread preserves over top. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture. Bake 20 to 25 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: tortilla sandwiches
directions: On one tortilla, place Cheddar cheese.
Place other tortilla on top.
Fry in oil until brown.

title: fancy pork chops
directions: Trim fat
from	chops.	Fry
and
remove
from skillet. Place potatoes
in a baking dish and sprinkle with onion, salt and pepper.
Place
chops
over
this.	Mix soup and water and pour over all the mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: yellow corn and rice casserole
directions: Cook yellow rice according to package directions.
Mix in cream of chicken soup and Mexicorn.
Pour in a buttered casserole dish.
Place cheese on top and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Combine raisins and water in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool (do not drain). Mix
and
cream
shortening
and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.

title: betty's banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs.
Add mashed bananas and beat well.
Sift white flour, soda, baking powder and salt together; add to the creamed mixture.
Add whole wheat flour. Do not sift the whole wheat flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli with a little salt until tender.
Drain.
Melt margarine in a pan and add flour to make roux.
Stir well.
Cook 5 minutes.
Blend in cream, stirring constantly, to make a smooth sauce.
Add stock and cook to make desired creamed soup consistency.
Add broccoli and cheese; mix well.

title: bread and butter pickle chips
directions: Rinse pickles in cold water.
Place pickles in a large jar or bowl. Cover with cold water.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 8 hours. Drain pickles. Add vinegar, water and sugar or substitute.
Put back in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before serving.

title: baked beans
directions: Peel onions and place in a baking dish with a little water and butter. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Add salt to taste.

title: hawaiian cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt; add scalded milk gradually. Cook on low heat until thickened.
Pour small amount over 3 beaten egg yolks, then add to the remainder.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes.
Add oleo, lemon juice, pineapple (drained) and add Baker's coconut. Pour into 10-inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue. Brown at 350° until golden brown.

title: hanky-panky
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet.
Add cheese, garlic salt, oregano and worcestershire sauce.
Heat and stir until cheese melts.
Spread mixture on bread (about 1 tsp. per slice). Garnish with tomatoes for color and added flavor, if desired. Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 70.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat butter, margarine and sugar together.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Add 1/2 of filling and then rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed pear salad
directions: Peel, half and core pears.
Stuff with cream cheese and blue cheese mixture (equal quantity of each).
Place pears face down on a bed of watercress on individual salad plates.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine, powdered sugar, egg, almond extract and vanilla. Blend in rest of ingredients with hands.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: microwave roasted potato wedges
directions: In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, cook oil, garlic, salt and paprika on High, 30 to 40 seconds.
Stir in browning sauce.
Cut unpeeled potatoes into 6 wedges.
Add wedges to oil in dish, stirring to coat all sides.
Cook covered 15 to 18 minutes on High.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix. Mixture should be crumbly. Save 1 1/2 cups of this mixture for the topping. Pat remaining crumb mixture into a ungreased pan. Combine peanut butter and marshmallow creme together. Spread over the crumb mixture. Crumble the 1 1/2 cups cake mixture over all and bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs until creamy; add oleo, beat well.
Cream in sugar and add vinegar.
Fold in fruit and pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Peel potatoes and cut into 1-inch cubes. Wash potatoes after peeling.
Mix cheese, flour, salt and pepper in paper sack.
Put wet potatoes in sack; shake to coat.
Put potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle any cheese, flour, salt and pepper left in sack over potatoes.
One medium onion, sliced into rings, can be added if you desire.
Cook one hour, uncovered, until tender and brown.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Sift flour once and measure.
Add baking powder, salt and sugar.
Sift again.

title: microwave spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine meat, mushrooms, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook on 100 percent power (High) for 6 to 8 minutes or until no pink remains, stirring twice.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano, basil, thyme, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Cook, covered, on High, for 10 to 12 minutes or until boiling.
Cook, uncovered, on 50 percent power (Medium) about 20 minutes or to desired consistency, stirring once.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan carrot cake
directions: Chop 1/2 cup pecans fine. Grease 3 (9-inch) layer cake pans well. Sprinkle each with about 2 1/2 tablespoons pecans to coat. Chop remaining pecans a little more coarsely. Set aside. Re-sift flour with baking powder and salt. Combine sugar, eggs, oil and cinnamon. Beat at high speed until light and well mixed. Add HALF of flour mixture. Stir until well blended. Add milk, then remaining flour. Stir in carrots and chopped pecans. Divide batter evenly in pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until cakes test done. Let stand in pans on wire racks 10 minutes. Turn cakes out onto racks to cool. When cold, frost with a Cream Cheese Frosting. Decorate with pecan halves. Makes 1 large cake or 12 servings.

title: white grapes in sour cream
directions: Select well-ripened, large seedless white grapes.
Stem, wash and allow to dry thoroughly.
If using brandy or other liqueur, add 1 to 2 tablespoons to grapes and mix gently.
Carefully mix in sour cream until grapes are coated.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
To serve, spoon grapes into dessert dishes and sprinkle lightly with brown sugar.

title: peach jelly
directions: Boil selected peach peeling.
Drain 4 cups juice.
Strain through cloth or filter.
Put in enamel pan.
Bring the juice to a rolling boil.
Add the Sure-Jell.
Bring to a rolling boil again. Add the sugar and stir with a wooden spoon.
Bring to a rolling boil that cannot be stirred down, for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: clam-cheese spread
directions: Blend everything in a food processor, adding the clams last. This keeps very well in a refrigerator container and tastes better the second day. Serve with sea rounds or Melba toast. Makes 2 pounds.

title: bean dip
directions: Combine ingredients over heat and serve with Doritos chips.

title: marie's pot pie
directions: Mix celery soup, chicken soup and Veg-All in bowl.
Add water or vegetable juice as needed.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put other pie shell on top.
Seal and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until pie crust is browned.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together and let sit for 5 minutes.
Drop by spoonful onto biscuit pan.
Bake at 400 degrees until brown on bottom and then turn on broil and brown top.

title: orange salad 1
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Sprinkle gelatin over mixture and stir well.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts over salad.
Chill about 6 hours.

title: teriyaki wing dings(makes about 3 dozen)
directions: For marinade, combine all ingredients except chicken.
Place chicken in shallow dish; pour marinade over.
Cover; refrigerate 6 hours, turning occasionally.
Arrange chicken on rack in shallow pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes, basting occasionally with marinade.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add
eggs,
sugar
and
margarine; blend well. Mix soda,
baking
powder
and salt with flour.
Add to bananas and stir well until blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 1 large loaf.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels with 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine and press into bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400 degrees.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, whipped topping and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Mix well.
Spread in top of pretzel crust.
Mix gelatin according to package directions.
Refrigerate until almost set.
Add apples, pecans and strawberries.
Spoon on top of cream cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: corn stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise.
Cook in salted water for 10 minutes.
Carefully remove pulp.
Drain corn and zucchini pulp well, then combine with salt, onions and chives.
Pile mixture in zucchini shells and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, margarine and shortening; mix well. Add egg one by one.
Add lemon extract; mix well.
Add flour and 7-Up; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours; don't preheat oven.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, grapes and celery.
Mix and add remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Chill several hours. Serve cold.

title: cream cheese celery stuffer
directions: Cut celery into small chunks.
Stuff with a mixture of cream cheese and olives.

title: vegetable squares
directions: Unroll crescent rolls in a jellyroll pan.
Seal seams.
Bake at 350° for 7-12 minutes until puffy and golden brown.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle shredded cheeses over vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook until rolling boil.
Time 5 minutes.
Take off stove. Add 1/2 large jar marshmallow cream and 1/2 cup peanut butter.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream and marshmallows.
Drain fruits and add to marshmallows and sour cream.
Cool several hours.

title: lemon pie without milk
directions: Mix dry ingredients and add boiling water and boil until thick.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Add beaten egg yolks and pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.
Bake at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump in the pineapple.
Dump in the pie filling.
Dump the cake mix on top.
Add butter, sliced on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.

title: quick chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chips over simmering water, beat in sherry, salt and egg yolks.
Beat whites until stiff and fold into chocolate mixture. Pour into 6 glasses and refrigerate 4 hours.

title: mom's hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat chocolate, butter and evaporated milk in the top of a double boiler over boiling water until the chocolate is melted. Add sugar and stir until dissolved. Continue heating over boiling water for another 20 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cool and serve over ice cream. Stores well in the refrigerator.
Can be easily reheated in the microwave or on the stove. Delicious!

title: bean and cheese dip
directions: Mix and heat in microwave or on stove.
Best served warm with Tostitos chips.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn relish salad
directions: Mix and chill at least 2 hours.

title: gingered ham slices
directions: Remove fat and slice into 1 to 1 1/4-inch slices.
Place ham in shallow dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ham. Refrigerate overnight with occasional basting.
Remove ham from marinade.
Grill each side 15 minutes, basting occasionally. Serve with marinade spooned over ham slices.
Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: atlanta apple salad
directions: Core apples and cube. Mix with lemon juice. Add next 3 ingredients. Combine sour cream and mayonnaise. Mix with fruit and toss well. Add chopped pecans; mix well.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Fold in strawberries, pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Put half of the mixture in a large 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Refrigerate until firm.
Cover this with a layer of Cool Whip, then a layer of strawberry mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Put 1 tablespoon butter in iron skillet on medium heat.
Add sugar, cocoa and flour; stir until all mixed.
Separate eggs and mix the yolks with milk and vanilla.
Add to dry mixture and stir until thick on medium heat.
When mixture is thick, empty into pie shell.
May use whites of eggs for a meringue.
Then bake in oven until meringue is lightly browned.

title: royal velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine baking soda and vinegar and let set. Combine other ingredients thoroughly and add baking soda/vinegar mixture last. Bake for 30 minutes.

title: patty's lemon sugar cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda.
Mix sugar, butter, eggs, vanilla and lemon.
Combine the two mixtures and chill.
Roll out and cut. Bake at 350°.

title: bird feeders
directions: Mix together and pack into pine cones.
Roll in bird seed. Prepare to hang by tying a netted bag around them.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dice apples; add to drained fruit cocktail.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Save enough nuts to sprinkle on top.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Chill for at least 1/2 hour.

title: low calorie tomato aspic
directions: Heat tomato soup and
1 cup V-8 juice to boiling point. Add Jell-O.
Dissolve the
plain gelatin in 1/2 cup V-8 juice; then add to the	Jell-O	mixture
with the remaining V-8.
Add other ingredients;
pour	in
mold and chill until firm.	This will keep for several days.

title: broccoli cheese salad
directions: Toss broccoli, cheese, onions and bacon.
Pour dressing over mixture about 30 minutes before serving.
Very good and serves about 12.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook the broccoli and onion in a little water until tender. Drain off the water.
Add the mushroom soup and 1 soup can of milk; heat until it is hot (not boiling).
Add the cheese and stir until it is melted.

title: party meatballs
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Season to taste.
Form into small meatballs.
Brown meatballs in a large skillet over medium heat.
