Drain off excess fat.
Combine chili sauce and jelly; blend and add to skillet.
Cook about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan.
Measure all ingredients into large bowl and blend.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
I use a Bundt pan.
Ice with vanilla icing.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine in 2 quart saucepan.
Add brown sugar, salt, corn syrup and water.
Heat to boiling.
Boil for 5 minutes watching carefully so sauce does not boil over.
Remove from heat and add baking soda; stir well.
Pour over popped corn and stir until well-coated.
Place on 2 cookie sheets and bake at 250° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake both batches at the same time.
Take caramel corn off cookie sheets immediately after removing from oven.
Pour into a large bowl.
This is great for parties!

title: cheese strata
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour butter into mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; blend.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Great brunch entree!

title: chocolate fudge goodie cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a saucepan and let come to a boil. Remove from heat and stir in sugar and flour.
Add soda to buttermilk, then add buttermilk to ingredients in saucepan.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Batter will be very thin.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan at 400° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Let cake cool in pan about 15 minutes, then add topping. Cover and let set for 6 hours.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form small balls and bake at 350° (usually about 20 minutes).

title: caramel cake
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water (234° on candy thermometer).
Remove from heat and beat until smooth.
Cool and spread between layers and on top.
Decorate top with nuts, if desired.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Serve as salad or dessert.

title: wilson's specialty cheese dip
directions: Melt all ingredients in a crock-pot.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Soften onions and peppers in boiling water; then drain. Mix with all
other ingredients except margarine and crackers. Put into a 9
x
13-inch baking dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Spread cracker mix over vegetables in baking dish.
Bake	20
to 30 minutes at 350° until cracker mix has browned and cheese has bubbled.

title: pasta puttanesca
directions: Cook pasta until done. Fry garlic, capers, olives, anchovies, chiles and oregano in a little olive oil for 3 to 4 minutes. Add tomatoes and cook on a simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add drained pasta and toss through. Top with fresh basil and good olive oil.

title: very tasty baked spuds
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice in half lengthwise.
Pat surfaces dry with paper towels and spread with butter.
Sprinkle each with salad dressing mix and cheese.
Bake cut-side down on a cookie sheet at 400° for 35 minutes until tender.
Dust with paprika.

title: black bean salad
directions: Soak beans overnight; drain.
Combine beans, water and 1/4 teaspoon of the cayenne.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until beans are tender (about 1 hour).
Drain.
Rinse until water runs clear and beans are cool.
Drain well.

title: philly pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese until creamed.
Add vanilla.
Add a little flour slowly, then some egg.
Continue to add flour and eggs; blend well.
Pour into a well-greased tube or Bundt pan.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it springs back when pressed with finger.

title: canned pickle peaches
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, water, cinnamon and cloves and boil for 5 minutes.
Add peaches.
Simmer 10 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Put in clean jars and cover with syrup and seal.

title: pear tree spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well, and store in airtight container.
This is a dry mix.
For individual servings, mix 3 Tbsp. per cup of hot water.
For group servings, stir 1 cup of mix per 12 cups of hot water.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients lightly.
Put half in buttered 12 x 8-inch casserole.
Mix next 6 ingredients thoroughly.
Put in casserole over bread mixture.
Top with remaining bread mixture. Mix beaten eggs with milk.
Pour evenly over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Take out of refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: cucumbers in sour cream
directions: Slice cucumbers thin.
Cover with salt.
Let stand in plenty of ice in bowl for about an hour.
Drain thoroughly; add to Sour Cream Dressing as follows:

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in a large bowl. Boil oleo, cocoa and water together and add to dry ingredients. Mix eggs, vanilla, buttermilk and soda together and add to batter. Bake on a large cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 375°. Frost as soon as you bring it out of the oven.

title: deluxe chipped beef
directions: Melt butter; add onion and cook.
Add torn chipped beef and cook until frizzled.
Blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Add sour cream, mushrooms, cheese and parsley.
Blend.
Heat to serving temperature and serve over toast or scrambled eggs.
Garnish.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni for 20 minutes in boiling salted water. Drain well and put back in the saucepan on a very low heat, with the butter and the milk.
Let the macaroni absorb the milk.
Then add the peppers and the dry mustard; mix well each time.
Add the cheese (except 2 to 3 tablespoons), remove from the heat and beat until it is all creamy.
Finally add the well beaten egg, pour into a greased ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese on top and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Just enough to let it set.
Put under a broiler for couple of minutes to brown the top, if desired.
The sauce should be curdy and creamy.
It can be served with a few drops of Tabasco sauce.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: beef brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
On a cutting board, mash the garlic and 1/2 tsp. of the salt together with the flat side of a knife into a paste.
Add the rosemary and continue to mash until incorporated. Put the garlic-rosemary paste in a small bowl and add 3 Tbsp. of olive oil; stir to combine.
Season both sides of the brisket with a fair amount of kosher salt and ground black pepper.
Place a large roasting pan or Dutch oven over medium high heat and coat with the remaining olive oil.
Put the brisket in the roasting pan and sear to form a nice brown crust on both sides.
Lay the vegetables all around the brisket and pour the rosemary paste over the whole thing.
Add the wine (beef broth) and tomatoes; toss in the parsley and bay leaves.
Cover the pan tightly with aluminum foil and transfer to the oven.
Bake for about 3 to 4 hours, basting every 30 minutes with the pan juices, until the beef is fork tender.
Remove the brisket to a cutting board and let rest for 15 minutes.
Scoop the vegetables out of the roasting pan and onto a platter, cover to keep warm.
Pour out some of the excess fat and put the roasting pan with the juices on the stove over medium high heat.
Boil and stir for 5 minutes until the sauce is reduced by 1/2.
(If you want a thicker sauce, mix 1 Tbsp. flour with 2 Tbsp. of wine or water and blend into the gravy.)
Slice the brisket across the grain (the muscle lines) at a slight diagonal. Serve with Crispy Potato Pancakes.
(Recipe in Vegetable Section.)

title: nut crusted pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Flour a Bundt pan, sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs yolks, one at a time.
Stir in remaining ingredients just until combined.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: Boil chicken with chopped onion and celery.
Remove chicken and dice.
Reserve stock.
Brown sausage with green onions, bell peppers and garlic.

title: kev's cocktail sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients. Chill.

title: molded orange cream salad
directions: Defrost frozen orange juice concentrate. Turn into a small bowl the contents of package of orange flavored gelatin. Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is dissolved. Add lemon juice, then the orange concentrate. Stir quickly to combine. Pour 1/2 cup of the gelatin mixture into a 5 or 6-cup mold. If necessary, chill remainder of gelatin. It should be of a heavy, syrupy consistency.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Mix together and chill dough. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in a 400° oven. Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into hush puppies or walnut size balls.
Fry until golden brown.
Serves 24.

title: bacon-cheese ring
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain well and crumble into small pieces.
In a medium mixing bowl, combine bacon, cheese, green onions, mayonnaise and cayenne.
Mix thoroughly.
Place almonds in the bottom of an oiled 7-cup ring mold.
Press cheese mixture into mold. Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold cheese ring onto platter. Place a small custard cup filled with strawberry preserves in the center of the ring.
Serve with crackers or French bread slices. Yields 20 to 25 servings.

title: daisy's crab casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a buttered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, cooking oil, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in oats, then corn flakes. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Use a very large bowl.
These cookies freeze well.
May add 1 small package peanut butter chips. Makes 8 or 9 dozen cookies.

title: crock-pot recipe steamed rye bread(extra moist; a favorite brown bread.)
directions: Thoroughly combine ingredients.
Pour into well-greased Bread 'n Cake Bake* pan and cover.
Pour 1/2 cup water in crock-pot and set pan inside.
Cover and steam on high 2 1/2 to 4 hours.
(I steam mine 4 1/2 to 5 hours.)

title: barbecue meatballs(serves 2)
directions: Combine beef,
egg, 3/4 cup Rice Krispies, salt, pepper and onion;
mix
well.	Mix
together
brown
sugar,
ketchup, nutmeg and mustard;
add
1/2 of sauce to beef mixture and mix well. Shape beef	mixture
into
balls and place in muffin tins.
Top balls with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Rice Krispies.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin piquant
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Trim fat from meat, place into a shallow dish, rub all over with mustard.
Mix together chicken broth, lime juice, salt, allspice and pepper.
Pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 6 hours.
Remove meat from marinade, place on a rack in roasting pan, coat with brown sugar.
Roast at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes (internal temperature should be 165° to 170°).

title: baby ruth cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour, salt, soda, vanilla and candy bar.
Chill.
Mold dough by hand to form 1/2-teaspoon drops.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 50 to 70 cookies.

title: easy hors d' oeuvres sauce
directions: Combine all of the above and pour over cream cheese.
Serve with Ritz Crackers.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and sausage together; add grated cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Form into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked cake doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening
and sugar.
Add egg, milk and dry ingredients. Bake in muffin pans
(makes
in 375° oven, about 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from pan immediately and roll in 5 tablespoons melted margarine, then in a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients using only 1/2 can of fried onions. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes. Add the rest of the fried onions and bake 5 more minutes.

title: parmesan garlic chicken
directions: Mix cheese, garlic powder and Italian dressing mix.
Moisten chicken breast and coat with seasoning mix.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake at 400° for 25 to 25 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, pour in 2-quarts ginger ale.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine milk and water in small saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Place 4 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Mix 15 seconds.
Gradually add warm liquids to flour mixture, about 30 seconds.
Mix 1 minute longer. Add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time.
Knead dough. Dough will be very sticky. Spread dough into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans that have been greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise in warm place, free from drafts, for 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Remove from pans immediately and cool on wire racks.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Lightly coat 3 large (19 ounce) cans with vegetable oil. Measure into large bowl ingredients in order given.
Mix thoroughly and fill each can 2/3 full.
Let batter rise for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool the "baking tins" until you can handle them easily, then slide a thin bladed knife around the loaves and shake them out.
Allow to cool thoroughly.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients until thick.
Pour over salad.
Can be made ahead of time and stored in refrigerator.

title: alice's deviled eggs
directions: Slice them. Mash egg yolks, mostly mayo, little mustard and some Kraft sandwich spread. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sinful cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped vegetables
directions: Add onion to mixed vegetables and cook until barely tender. Drain.
Add margarine and cheese.
Stir until blended.
Put in oblong casserole dish.
Crumble Ritz crackers and 1/4 stick margarine and top casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix together bran, milk and raisins.
Let stand 10 minutes. Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat together egg, sugar, molasses and oil.
Add bran, milk and raisin mixture.
Add flour mixture.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: ranch chicken breasts
directions: Whisk juice and dressing mix together.
Marinate breasts in 1/2 juice mixture for 2 to 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: oatmeal cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine oats, wheat flour, brown sugar, salt and margarine in a large bowl.
Pour over boiling water and stir in to combine. Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
When the batter is cooled to lukewarm, add the yeast and stir in white flour.
When dough is stiff enough to handle turn onto floured board and knead 5-10 min. Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into roll - flatten slightly and put 1 tsp. cinnamon/sugar in middle.
Shape into roll and place in a greased pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes.
Cool on rack, brush rolls with margarine for a soft crust.

title: doritos cheese toast
directions: Put one good handful of cheese Doritos on a cooked cheese toast.
Fold cheese toast in half after putting Doritos on toast. Eat to your hearts desire.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, green onions, watercress and peas or vegetable mix.
Place spinach on top of all the other mixture. Let it stand overnight.
Stir all ingredients together and serve.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add water and 2 cups blueberries; cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened and clear.
Stir in butter and lemon juice; cool.
Place the remaining blueberries in baked pie shell; top with the cooked berry mixture.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: cooked cereal cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add cooked cereal, then add all dry ingredients.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.

title: taco macaroni
directions: Brown beef and drain grease.
Add taco seasoning.
Stir, then add tomatoes and water.
Add macaroni and simmer a few minutes.

title: banana peanut butter cream pie
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water; set aside.
In saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup cold milk.
Stir in remaining milk, sugar and butter; simmer for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Gradually add hot mixture to eggs, stirring well.
Return egg mixture to saucepan; cook and stir until thickened (do not boil).
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Blend in peanut butter.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour half of the filling into pie shell.
Add bananas; top with remaining filling.
Garnish with additional whipped topping rosettes, if desired.

title: white yeast bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1 cup of water; let stand. Combine 5 cups of water, salt, sugar and shortening; add yeast mixture and 1 cup of flour.
Beat on high for 1 minute, then hand mix, a little at a time, the rest of the flour.
Knead for 10 minutes on floured board or table.
Place in a greased bowl; let rise until doubled in size, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: crisp crusted baked chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl mix potato flakes, garlic and Parmesan cheese.
Roll chicken in egg mix, then in the potato mix.
Melt butter in shallow baking pan.
Roll coated chicken pieces in the butter and place them skin side up in pan. Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes or until juices from chicken run clear.

title: favorite pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pie shell.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Combine eggs and milk in bowl; beat thoroughly.
Dip chops in mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
Place in greased baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until chops are golden brown.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand several hours before serving. Makes 10 to 12 servings.
Broccoli seems to absorb all the mayonnaise for a crisp fresh salad.

title: aunt denny's orange dressing
directions: Shake, beat or blend.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Shake well before using.
Good dressing for greens, mandarin oranges, red onion slices and cashews.

title: church cake
directions: Do not use mixer.
Blend with a spoon.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients until all are mixed well. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Place foil over cake top for the last 20 minutes to prevent cracking.
Cool.
Place in refrigerator overnight before slicing.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 8 to 10.
Enjoy!

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together and add to the undrained crushed pineapple.
Stir in the shredded cheese and place mixture in buttered casserole.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mexican potatoes
directions: Cut up potatoes in chunks; place in a shallow 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Put cheese, onion and pimento on top of potatoes. Sprinkle on parsley, paprika and garlic powder.
Put toasted bread cubes on top; drizzle butter on top of toast.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mini quiche
directions: In a large skillet, cook onion and garlic in butter or margarine until onion is tender but not brown.
Add zucchini or broccoli and stir about 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat.

title: strawberry yogurt whip
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until beginning to thicken.
Add low-fat yogurt and beat with beater until light and fluffy.
Pour into individual dessert cups or punch cups.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine all ingredients with rice in 3 cups of water.
Cook about 40 minutes.
Cover and let sit until ready to serve.
Serve with other food where dressing could have been used.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill a buttered baking dish 3/4 deep with apples.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Dot generously with butter.
Place in 350° oven while mixing dough.
Then mix sugar, salt, flour, baking powder and cut in butter.
Add well beaten egg.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Spreads self in oven.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 325° to 350°.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together, except catsup.
Pat into a 9-inch square pan.
Spread catsup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butternut squash puff
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans; mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2-inch water in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and place casserole in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Garnish with pecans.

title: very easy peach cobbler
directions: If using fresh peaches, add additional 1/4 cup of sugar with them.
Drain canned peaches if being used.
Put butter in a deep pan.
Melt at 350° in oven.
Stir up batter of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Put peaches on top.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour or until golden brown. Batter rises to top while baking.
Can substitute canned cherries, blueberries or fruit cocktail for peaches.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil fryer or hen and debone.
Mix chicken soup into your broth.
Combine flour and water and knead to a stiff ball.
Roll out very thin and cut into squares.
Bring broth back to a slow rolling boil and drop dumplings in, one at a time.
(It will make a layer on top and you simply press down with fork or spoon.)
Salt and pepper to taste.
After you have placed all dumplings in pot, boil for 1 minute and turn heat off.
Let dumplings sit for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: pita pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place pita breads on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each with 2 Tbsp. pizza sauce, spreading to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Top each with onion, bell pepper and mushrooms. Sprinkle each with 1/4 c. cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Makes 4 pizzas.

title: apple crunch pie
directions: Place rack in lowest position. Preheat oven to 425°.
Spoon apple filling into pastry shell. Bake 15 minutes.

title: cider chicken casserole
directions: Coat chicken lightly with flour.
Heat oil in large pan and brown chicken a bit at a time.
Remove chicken and put aside. Saute onions in same pan, adding a little cider if needed.

title: cream cheese pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, salt, vanilla and 1 egg in bowl.
Beat until well blended; pour into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine 3 eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and corn syrup in bowl; blend well. Pour over pecans.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Chop broccoli into bite size pieces.
Tear bread into 1-inch pieces.
In bowl, beat with a fork, eggs, milk, melted butter, cheese and salt.
Pour cheese mixture over broccoli.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: caramel fudge
directions: Bring 3 cups sugar and milk to 212°.
Add melted sugar. Cook to soft ball.
Cool.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: zesty cheese ball
directions: Grind olives and Cheddar cheese cubes in a large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix until creamy.
Cover bowl and chill thoroughly.
Shape into a ball.
Roll in parsley or nuts. Serve with crackers or bread sticks.
Yields 1 1/2-pound cheese ball.

title: cajun dirty rice
directions: Place gizzards in a medium-sized saucepan.
Add water to barely cover.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes or until gizzards are tender.
Set aside with cooking liquid.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix milk and pudding following directions on box.
After pudding sets, fold in Cool Whip.

Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Line with whole graham crackers. Layer on 1/2 of pudding, another layer of crackers and a layer of the remaining pudding. Top with graham crackers. Frost and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: martin chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Melt chocolate in water on stove and add
to
creamed
mixture.
Add
soda to buttermilk, then add flour
and milk alternately to mixture.
Add vanilla, then eggs and mix (eggs must be added last or the cake will be ruined). Bake in 8-inch square or 9-inch round layers or in 9 x 13-inch pan at	350°
for
25 minutes.	May bake as cupcakes too.

title: super simple pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake according to instructions on box (9 x 13-inch or 9 x 15-inch).
While cake is baking, cook pineapple, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Spread mixture on baked cake while cake is warm.
Let cool.
Prepare pudding mix according to directions on box.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle with coconut.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large saucepan and bring to boil over medium/high heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Turn heat to low and cook until rice is softened, about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Blend beaten egg and 2 tablespoons of milk in small bowl.
Pour into Rice Pudding; blend well.
Pour in serving dish and chill before serving.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: ranch oyster quackers
directions: In a large covered plastic container, mix together salad oil, lemon pepper, dill weed and garlic salt.
Add oyster crackers and mix thoroughly.
DO NOT COOK!

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Add all spices and marinate for 12 hours.

title: fluffy gold cake
directions: Sift together into bowl, Softasilk, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, 2/3 cup milk, extract and vanilla.
Beat vigorously with spoon for 2 minutes by clock (about 150 strokes per minute).
Or mix with electric mixer on medium speed (middle of dial) for 2 minutes.
Add the rest of milk and egg yolks.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Pan size:
2 round layers, 8 x 1 1/2-inch.
Temperature:
350° (moderate oven). Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with White Mountain Icing.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a baking dish.
For batter, mix sugar, flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over the melted oleo. Then dump sliced peaches over the batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown and bubbling.

title: sunset punch
directions: Combine instant breakfast drink with pineapple juice and ginger ale in a 2-quart punch bowl, stirring until completely dissolved.
Garnish with mint leaves.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: special potato soup
directions: Saute celery, onion and butter in Dutch oven until tender. Add the next 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes, until vegetables are tender.
Remove from heat.
Mash with potato masher slightly (soup will be very lumpy).
Add milk and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Makes 10 cups.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given. Add nuts, if desired.

title: chicken cabbage salad
directions: Break and cook noodles according to directions on package. Cool.
In a large bowl, toss together noodles, cabbage, chicken, celery, onion and carrots. In small bowl whisk together oil, vinegar, sugar, sesame seed, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss until all ingredients are well coated.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: french vanilla fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, put all fruits except bananas and sprinkle with dry pudding.
Cover and chill.
Slice bananas.
Just before serving, add marshmallows and bananas.

title: creamy fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Serve over fruit.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: greek chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl combine chicken, cucumber, Feta cheese, olives and parsley; set aside.
In a small bowl stir together mayonnaise, yogurt, oregano and garlic.
Add to chicken mixture.
Toss to coat; cover and chill.
Serve in pita pockets with lettuce or serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine 3 cups milk and pudding mix.
Beat on low speed of electric mixer until thick.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: cookies and cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Butter a deep cake pan.
Coat with crushed Oreo cookie crumbs.
Beat together cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, 3 eggs (one at a time) and vanilla.
Stir in broken cookies.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let cool.
Turn out onto plate. Refrigerate before serving.
Garnish with fresh fruit.
Serves 8 generously.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Mix cooked macaroni, mushroom soup and tuna all together.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sauteed corn and mushrooms
directions: Cook mushrooms and onion in butter in skillet for about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and saute about 5 minutes longer.

title: horseradish cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in the top of a double boiler or in the microwave, stirring in horseradish and mayonnaise.
Let cool and refrigerate.

title: pineapple cake(no butter)
directions: Mix flour and sugar. Stir in eggs, soda, vanilla, chopped nuts and crushed pineapple and juice. Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pink lady
directions: Pour cherry juice into mixing bowl.
Mix, with blender, cream cheese with cherry juice until smooth.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Drain fruit cocktail and mandarin oranges.
Mix into cream cheese and Cool Whip mixture.
Cut cherries (about 1/2 jar) into halves and mix in with English walnuts.
Smooth top.
Cut rest of cherries in half and place on top.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to
Mix flour, margarine and powdered sugar. Press in an ungreased square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch or 9 x 9 x 2-inch), building up 1/2-inch edges.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Pour over hot crust and bake until no indentation remains when touched lightly in center, about 25 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into about 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes 25 cookies.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° until done.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt first 2 ingredients in pan.
Keep warm and set aside.
Mix the next 4 ingredients; pour 1/2 of the mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes. Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips and dollop on caramel mixture.
Pour the rest of the cake batter on top.
Bake an additional 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool and put in the refrigerator for 3 minutes before cutting!
Enjoy.

title: heavenly lime salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
cups
boiling
water in a large mixing bowl;
add hot jello mixture and stir until dissolved. Melt marshmallows
in
1/4 cup boiling water in top of double boiler; add
to
jello
mixture.
Add
1 cup cold water.
Add whipped cream and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts. Pour into a greased large baking dish.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl; beat until smooth.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn down to 350° and bake 25 minutes, or until knife will pull out uncoated.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to mixture alternately with milk and cocoa.
Beat until all ingredients are used up.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Good to use on all types of fruit.

title: potato chip or pretzel cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well by hand.
Take 1 teaspoon of dough and roll into balls; press down with fork.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and blueberry. Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: night before mashed potatoes
directions: Boil and drain potatoes. Whip hot potatoes, adding cream cheese and sour cream. Continue beating until fluffy and smooth. Add salt and pepper. Place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Dot generously with butter. Cover with foil and refrigerate. Bake, covered with foil, 15 minutes at 325°. Continue baking, uncovered, for 20 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onion, peppers and bacon (crushed).
Add scrambled eggs. Cook rice as directions state.
Add rice and soy sauce.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour.
Stir in buttermilk.
Knead slightly. Roll out to about 3/4 to 1-inch.
Cut into biscuits.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.
These freeze well before baking.

title: green delight
directions: Dissolve pudding in liquid from pineapple.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving a few cherries for the top, if desired. Chill well.
Good with turkey/dressing meal.

title: herb bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt, caraway seed, nutmeg, sage and 2 cups flour.
Blend well.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add remaining flour and beat until smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes or until double.
Stir down by beating 30 strokes.
Spread evenly in loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Smooth top with floured hands.
Cover and let rise 40 minutes or until double.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 45 minutes or until loaf sounds hollow when tapped.
Butter tops and remove from pan to cool.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 1 cup liquid.
Set pineapple aside.
In skillet combine pineapple liquid, onion, brown sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, bouillon and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken.
Reduce heat.
Tightly cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken.
Set aside.
Combine cornstarch and cold water. Stir into skillet.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add pineapple, orange sections and chicken.
Heat through.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
May be served with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: caramel fruit salad
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Add powdered sugar.
Add to remaining ingredients.
Cream together sugar and eggs; fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in pineapple, peanuts and apples.
Refrigerate. (Don't put in peanuts, if making ahead.)

title: beautiful cheddar braids
directions: *I used Sargento finely grated Mozzarella and Cheddar.

title: date nut squares
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients
on medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add one teaspoon vanilla, one cup chopped nuts and three cups Rice Krispies.
Put in greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into small squares. Then shake in bowl with confectioners sugar.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cook 5 minutes; pour on cake while hot.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda
and	salt.
Set aside.
Beat for 2 minutes shortening,
brown sugar, granulated sugar, egg, peanut butter, water and
vanilla.
Add
sifted flour mixture; beat 1 minute.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet and press lightly with a
fork
dipped
in flour.
Add chopped peanuts if desired.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pancakes
directions: You put butter, milk, flour, butter again, then syrup.
Put it on a plate.
Then you eat it.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and put topping on.

title: banana blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line muffin tins with paper baking cups.
In a large bowl, beat sugar and oil together, then add bananas, yogurt, vanilla and eggs.
Blend well.
In small bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add to banana mixture and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Gently stir in blueberries. Pour into tins.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Can also be baked in loaf pan for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: summer dessert
directions: Crumble cake in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread pineapple on cake, covering it well.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and spread on pineapple.
Cover pudding with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Garnish with cherries and nuts.

title: pineapple drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain pineapple.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Drop cookies on cookie sheet.
Cook for 12 minutes at 400°.
Cool and serve.

title: abgusht(bean soup)
directions: Rinse beans and set out the night before.
Place beans in stew pot.
Wash potato and put in stew pot (whole with peel).
Slice onion; add stew meat or lamb shank.
Add tomato sauce and enough water to fill pan 1/2 full.
Salt to taste.
Slow cook for 2 to 3 hours.
Remove any bones.
Peel potato.
Drain broth.
Mash all together.
Serve with chips or bread.

title: cheese cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar with cream cheese; add eggs, one at a time. Add salt and almond flavoring.
Pour into spring-form pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven; cool for 20 minutes. Mix sour cream, remaining sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cheese cake.
Bake for 10 minutes longer.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss gently to coat.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: easy low-fat crustless pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° if using glass pie plate).
Grease a 10-inch plate.
Beat all ingredients 2 minutes with a mixer.
Pour into plate.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Yields 8 servings.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: *Heat and thicken fruit or use canned pie filling.

title: skillet chicken with rice and vegetables
directions: Brown chicken on both sides; season with a little garlic and pepper.
Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions.
Slice and saute vegetables in margarine, garlic, pepper and red cooking wine.
Cut chicken into small pieces, mix in with Rice-A-Roni.
Mix chicken broth in with vegetables until heated, then pour over chicken and rice and serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until done.

Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish, celery seed and salt in small bowl and mix well. Place half the potatoes, onions and parsley in serving bowl. Spoon half of the sour cream mixture over the top.
Spoon remaining sour cream mixture over the next layer of potatoes. Sprinkle with remaining parsley over sour cream.
Chill in refrigerator for 12 hours or longer.

title: turnip puff
directions: Cook turnips until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and eggs.
Beat well.
(This much can be done the day ahead.)
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Stir.
Butter a casserole dish and put in mixture. Combine crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until light brown on top.
Serves 6. Enjoy!

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown the meat and onion in skillet.
Add drained beans and soup (do not add water to soup).
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mash potatoes with milk, egg and seasonings.
Drop in mounds over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baker's stew(alsatian)
directions: You will need an earthenware cooking pot, plus lid.

title: tex mex mix
directions: Spread bean dip for bottom layer, then avocado mixture.
Mix up taco seasoning with sour cream, then spread the sour cream. Add on top, any way, the cheese, tomatoes, olives and bell peppers.
Lemon juice goes with the avocados.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt, and mustard.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until smooth and thick.
Beat egg. Add small amount of sauce, stir, return to sauce.
Cook about one minute.
Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Place in one quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake covered at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: marinated cucumbers and onions
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions 6 hours in 1 tablespoon salt.
Drain off liquid.
Mix other ingredients and add to onions and cucumbers.
Keep refrigerated.
May be added to again and again as long as dressing lasts.

title: pumpkin pie squares
directions: Combine with mixer on low.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; beat well.
Add oil, flour, spices, soda and salt; beat well.
Add pumpkin.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice pudding
directions: Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish or baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 1/2 hour, without stirring.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Wash shrimp and set aside. Simmer sauce, onion, celery, green pepper, mushrooms, parsley and pepper in skillet for 30 minutes. Add shrimp and cook 10-15 minutes more, until shrimp is pink and tender. Serve over rice.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl. Add eggs, water, vanilla and shortening. Beat until smooth. Fold in oatmeal, pecans and raisins. Shape into balls or drop by teaspoon 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on wire rack. Makes 4 1/2 to 5 dozen.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Whip together eggs and milk.
Let stand overnight.
Add 1
can mushroom
soup mixed with a little milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: anise toast
directions: Beat together ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in bread pan.
Remove from oven and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Butter each slice lightly on both sides.
Place on cookie sheet and return to oven for 5 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before storing in tight lid container.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Chop nuts.
Beat eggs; add sugar and oil.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture with zucchini.
Stir in raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Put in 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans.
Bake in lowest rack at 350° for 60 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes and turn out on wire rack.
Glaze with powdered sugar mixed with a little cream.
This recipe freezes well.

title: diet raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and cook for few minutes.
Add butter to hot raisins; let cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Place crust on top, cut holes in top crust.
Bake about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Put peppers (discarding seeds) and peeled onions through food processor.
Add salt; cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drain liquid and discard.
Add vinegar and sugar to vegetables.
Bring to a boil, simmer 20 minutes.
Ladle into hot jars, adjust lids at once.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: san perido eggplant
directions: Trim skin off eggplant.
Slice into rounds 1-inch thick. Liberally oil cookie sheet with olive oil.
Place eggplant on cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven approximately 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove cookie sheet and top each eggplant round with 2 tablespoons of marinara sauce.
Return to oven for 5 minutes. Remove cookie sheet, top each round with 1 or 2 fresh basil leaves and sliced Provolone cheese (approximately 1 ounce each).
Turn off oven.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: bean bundles
directions: Arrange green beans in bunches of 8, wrapping 1/2 slice bacon around each bunch.
Place beans in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour dressing over beans.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Bake at 350° until bacon is brown on top.

title: great grandmother's raisin pie
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: squash fritters
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender and drain well.
Add salt, pepper, Tony's seasoning, egg and flour.
Mix well.
Drop in hot deep fat for fritters (like hush puppies) or shallow oil for patties.
Brown patties on both sides.
Drain well on paper towel. You don't have to cook these all at once.
Dough can be stored in refrigerator for a few days and cooked later.
I have made a "ton" of these!

title: tuna souffle
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in butter until tender (not brown).
Combine tapioca with milk and slightly beaten egg yolks. Cook until it comes to boil, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings and mix with drained tuna, green pepper, onion and celery.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry and fold in tuna mixture. Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole.
Place in pan of water and bake in 300° oven for about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with parsley and butter sauce.
Can also be made with crab meat.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and mix with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess moisture.
Add carrot and let stand.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat.
Stir in sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat for 2 minutes.
(Mixture should be bubbly; stir constantly.)
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix, then add peanut butter and mix again.
Add oatmeal.
Stir to coat. Drop from spoon onto waxed paper.

title: easy cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Put frozen rolls in pan.
Sprinkle with pudding mix, white sugar and cinnamon.
In a small pan melt butter with brown sugar and Karo syrup.
Bring to a "short" boil.
Add chopped nuts and pour over rolls.
Cover with foil, then a cloth. Next morning bake at 350° for 20 to 35 minutes.
Do not refrigerate overnight.
Loosen sides and flip over onto large serving plate.
Very easy and gooey.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and garlic in oil.
Add salt, pepper, oregano, chili powder, stewed tomatoes and tomato sauce. Simmer about 45 minutes until thick.
Cook noodles according to package directions.

title: grapefruit pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and salt until thick and clear. Add box of Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Chill until mixture begins to set.
Add grapefruit sections and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chicken joanne
directions: Combine sour cream and seasonings.
Marinate chicken for as long as possible, best overnight.
Dip in bread crumbs and arrange in ovenproof dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken and bake at 350° for one hour (40 minutes for boneless breasts).

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add scalded milk (cooled), salt and eggs.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix well adding yeast mixture last.
Place in greased bowl and let rise 1 hour.
Knead and roll out dough.
Cut with doughnut cutter and place on wax paper.
Let rise until double.
Fry and drain, then glaze with 1 box powdered sugar, 1/2 cup milk (scant) and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.

title: scalloped carrots with cheese
directions: Cook carrots until tender, drain and set aside.
Cook onion in butter in saucepan for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milk, do not boil. Stir in flour, salt and mustard, until thick and smooth, then add pepper and celery salt.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Arrange cooked carrots and cheese.
Pour sauce over carrots, top with crumbs and "dot" with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seafoam cole slaw
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Add vinegar, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper. Add salad dressing; blend well with hand beater.
Pour into bowl; chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in grated cabbage.
Pour into jello mold; set until firm.
Garnish with mandarin oranges or cherries.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Flatten chicken breasts by placing between two pieces of wax paper and using either a rolling pin or a meat mallet until they are about 1/4-inch thick.

title: cooked frosting
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients to soft ball, about 5 minutes. Take off stove; beat until creamy.
Add the vanilla.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve lemon jello, 1/2 cup hot water and 1 cup sugar. Cool.
Whip stiff 1 cup evaporated milk (have milk very cold). Fold in crushed pineapple.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Makes 2 pies.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix 1 egg, margarine and cake mix at high speed until crumbly; press into 9 x 13 pan. Mix condensed milk, 1 egg and vanilla; stir in pecans and chips. Pour over cake in pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Will be firm when cooked.

title: sopa de alondigas(meat ball soup)
directions: Blanch, peel and seed tomatoes.
Dice 3 of the tomatoes and set aside.
Crush the remaining tomatoes and simmer in the beef broth. After 30 minutes, strain the tomato pulp out of the broth.
Add bell pepper, onion, chili powder and diced tomatoes.
Simmer until vegetables are ready.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Melt oleo, milk and cocoa.
Mix together.
Pour into 2 uncooked pie shells and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Pour in glasses and serve.

title: strawberry-nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Stir just until the ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.

title: lo-cal lasagne
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown meat mixture.
Mix together cottage cheese and egg.
Add this to meat mixture with sauce, saving some sauce for top.

title: spiced coffee mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender; process 15 seconds or until blended.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: strawberry pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix and Jell-O together.
Add water, oil and eggs. Beat well and add berries and juice.
Beat.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a small bowl, beat eggs. In larger bowl, beat melted butter with syrup, sugar, salt and vanilla. Add eggs and mix well. Stir in pecans and pour into pie shells. Place your pie pans on a cookie sheet to prevent bottom from burning. Bake 10 minutes at 400° and then 30 additional minutes at 325°.

title: frosted lemonade punch
directions: In a punch bowl stir cold water into lemonade mix until dissolved.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Stir half of the sherbet to soften;
blend
into
lemonade
mixture.
Scoop
remaining sherbet on top.
Resting bottle on rim of bowl, carefully pour in carbonated beverage; stir gently.
Makes 14 cups.

title: seafari summer salad
directions: Mix together the day before serving.
Refrigerate.
Keeps well for at least 10 days.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° until firm and light brown.

title: clara moe's dill pickles
directions: Let this come to a boil and put on pickles hot. Put dill in bottom of jar, also in center and on top. Be sure and put liquid on hot and seal tight. You can put a little garlic in jar if you like that flavor.

title: watson's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine, sugars and eggs.
Add vanilla, baking powder and soda.
Add flour, nuts and chips.
Mix very well.
Add blended oats.
Bake at 375° until slightly golden brown.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Cook noodles, drain, rinse and drain.
Arrange in single layer until needed.
Lightly brown chicken in hot oil, add onions, cooked until tender and remove from heat.
Stir in chili powder, Ricotta and Jack cheese and egg.
Spoon 1/4 cup to 1/3 cup mixture on noodle and roll up.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Pour salsa over roll ups.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serve if desired with sour cream, sliced olives and chopped tomatoes.

title: pecan pie or coconut
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs, cream, syrup, nutmeg and vanilla flavoring.
Stir in 1 cup pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and top with dots of butter.
Bake at 350° until thick.

title: frosted fruit mold
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water; allow to cool.
Add soda pop and chill until partially set.
Add drained pineapple and banana. Chill until firm.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Stir in egg and the reserved pineapple syrup.
Cook over low heat until thick. Chill.
Whip the cream and fold into chilled sauce.
Spread on top of gelatin mold.
Sprinkle with cheeses.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, cinnamon and salt in thick skillet and cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly until mixture blends and bubbles.
Arrange sweet potatoes in skillet; cover and cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Uncover; cook about 5 minutes longer, basting frequently until potatoes are glazed.

title: apricot salad
directions: In small pan, put first 4 ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Cool. Add next 3 ingredients.
When partially set, fold in the Dream Whip.
Chill.

title: betty's potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes in a deep casserole with onions and butter. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add milk to cover.
Bake at 325° until potatoes are done and mixture has started to thicken.
Sauce will thicken some on standing.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix and fill paper-lined muffin pans 2/3 full. Combine cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add egg and salt, beating well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spoon 1 heaping teaspoonful into center of each cupcake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then cool on a wire rack.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen, approximately.

title: "no-bake" baked beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp enough to crumble.
Remove from skillet and drain on paper towel.
Reserve bacon grease.
Place pork and beans in medium saucepan.
Add catsup, chopped onion, brown sugar and 1 tablespoon bacon grease.
Crumble crisp bacon into beans and stir.
Cook over medium-high heat until boiling, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: bean pot baked lentils
directions: Rinse lentils; drain.
Combine in saucepan lentils, onion and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar, catsup, molasses and oil.
Turn into 1-quart bean pot or casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: moist and fruity rainbow cake
directions: Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean layer pans; prick each cake with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve each flavor gelatin separately in 1 cup of the boiling water.
Carefully pour one flavor gelatin over one cake layer and the other flavor gelatin over second cake layer.
Chill 3 or 4 hours.

title: jello salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix Jell-O, sugar and cream cheese with electric mixer.
Add boiling water slowly.
Add 3/4 of Cool Whip. Add fruit cocktail (juice included).
Mix well.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight or until set.
Frost with remaining Cool Whip.

title: teriyaki sauce
directions: Carve steak into thin slices.
Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight.
Grill or saute until done to your liking.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until Foamy.
Add cornstarch, flour, and sugar. Mix well.
Heat 1 qt. milk, add egg mixture.
Bring to slow boil stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Cool add cream, vanilla, salt, and remaining milk.
Pour in ice cream freezer. Makes 1 gallon.

title: lemon custard cloud(tart and tangy; rich, yet light!)
directions: Place egg yolks, lemon juice and Fruit Sweet in small saucepan.
In small dish dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add this to lemon mixture.
Blend in potato flakes.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cooled lemon mixture.
Tear cake into walnut size pieces and fold into lemon mixture.
Spoon into dessert glasses or glass square pan.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: plain pie crust
directions: Cut shortening in flour and salt until pieces are the size of small peas.
Sprinkle water over mixture.
Form into ball.
Place on pastry board.
Roll out for an 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden brown.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Pour over Rice Chex.
In a large container with a lid, put Rice Chex and 2 cups powdered sugar; shake.
Store in airtight container. Makes a great and fun snack for kids!

title: french toast casserole
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add brown sugar and cook until syrupy (don't worry if the brown sugar does not completely blend with the butter).
Pour mixture into a 9x13-inch pan.
Slice bread into 12 slices, about 1-inch thick, and place over sugar/butter mixture, completely lining the bottom of pan with slices.
Beat eggs, milk and vanilla and pour over bread slices.
Cover dish and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake in preheated 350-degree oven for 45 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar over top when ready to serve.
Pass the warmed syrup.
OR skip the syrup and use your favorite "Simply Fruit" and sprinkle only a tiny bit of powdered sugar.

title: cheesy zucchini
directions: Cook the first three ingredients together for 5 minutes, then drain well.
Combine the remaining ingredients and then fold in 1 1/2 cups crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake in a greased shallow pan at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: halupsi
directions: Boil cabbage, separate leaves and set aside. Mix rice, onions, peppers, carrots, meat, salt and pepper. Wrap 1/2 cup mixture in cabbage; leaf; and place in greased casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup water over this.
Bake 90 minutes at 350°.
Stir tomato soup and sour cream together.
Pour over Halupsi and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves six.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar together. Then add rest of ingredients. Pour into uncooked 9-inch pastry shell. Bake in a 450° oven for 5 minutes. Reduce temperature to 325° and bake another 25 to 38 minutes or until filling is firm. Cool on rack.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening; add sour milk with soda and mix.
Add flour and mix; add the cocoa mixture to batter.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: boneless chicken with croutons
directions: Place boneless chicken in bottom of shallow 13 x 9-inch pan (thinned out).
Place a piece of cheese on each piece of chicken. Cover all the chicken with cheese.
Combine in a bowl the soup and water.
After mixing, spread evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle croutons over entire top of pan.
Drizzle melted butter over top of pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare lettuce, tomatoes and cucumbers as you would for tossed salad.
Add cheese, beans and corn chips.
Stir as you add Catalina dressing.
Use enough to cover all ingredients.
Mix all ingredients well.
May use more or less of ingredients, according to your preference.
Salad is better if dressing is added just before serving.

title: lane's applesauce
directions: Quarter apples; place in pot with water (enough to see, but not to cover apples).
Cook at medium heat, covered, until soft mush.
Press through colander.
Put back on stove.
Add plenty of sugar to taste.
Boil, then cool and add vanilla.

title: santa's whiskers cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat in the milk and vanilla. Add chopped cherries and walnuts.
Fold in flour.
Form dough into 2 eight-inch logs.
Roll in coconut and wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Chill well.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet in 375° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Add shortening, salt, sugar and yeast to water. Stir until shortening is melted. Stir in flour; cover and set in warm place. When doubled in size, add eggs. Knead; let rise again until doubled in size. Roll out 1/2 inch thick on well floured board. Cut with biscuit cutter 2-inch in diameter; crease in center with a dull knife. Brush with melted butter and fold over, pinching the dough at sides to make a pocketbook. Place on baking dish and brush top with melted butter. Let rise and bake in hot oven (400°) about 20 minutes. Makes 24 rolls.

title: microwave onion herb bread
directions: Cut loaf in 1-inch thick slices without cutting through bottom crust.
Blend remaining ingredients, except paprika, in small bowl.
Spread on bread slices.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place loaf on paper towel lined microproof plate.
Cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until heated through.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients, one at a time as follows:
lettuce, pepper, celery, onion, peas, salad dressing, sugar, cheese and bacon.
Do not toss.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake; let cool. Make Jello. Punch holes in cake with fork. Pour Jello over top of cake with ladle. Chill overnight in refrigerator. Cut into squares when ready to serve.

title: deer or beef salami
directions: Mix everything together and roll into sausage shape.
Wrap in foil, prick foil with a fork.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake on rack of a broiler pan in the oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Wrap in new foil and refrigerate for 24 hours before eating.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a Pam sprayed casserole dish.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take out and place biscuits on top.
Return to oven at 425° until biscuits are done.
Serve warm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When done remove skin and grate cooked potatoes.
Add cream of chicken soup, sour cream, margarine, onion, salt and pepper.
Grate cheese and put most in, but reserve a little for topping.
Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Crumble potato chips and cheese on top.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: dottie's dumplings
directions: Mix
together, roll thin and cut in 1-inch wide strips. Drop in
boiling broth.
Add a little pepper.
Cover and watch as it will boil over.
After a few minutes, turn heat down and cook until tender (about 15 minutes).
Recipe may be doubled. Can add 1/2 cup milk just before turning heat off.

title: batter way rolls
directions: Put water in large bowl; add yeast.
Let stand a few minutes. Stir.
Add shortening, salt, sugar, egg and half of flour.
Beat 1 minute.
Add rest of flour.
Set in warm place.
Let rise about 30 minutes.
Grease 1 1/2 dozen muffin pans.
Fill 1/2 full.
Let rise to top.
Bake in hot oven.

title: mystery cheesecake
directions: Pour cake mix into 9 x 12 x 2 floured and greased pan.
In same bowl, mix by hand Ricotta, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Spread evenly on top of cake mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool (sprinkle with confectioners sugar, when serving).
(Better second day than first.)
Freezes well!

title: italian beef
directions: Put beef and broth into crock-pot; salt and pepper. Add spices and peppers. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours. Remove meat and slice thin. Put back in crock-pot to cook another hour. Serve on deli rolls.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Pour ingredients in greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: buffet onion casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan or equal baker.
Layer 1/2 the onions, 1/2 the chips and 1/2 the cheese.
Whip up 1 can soup and pour over.
Repeat layers up to soup. Mix the 2nd can of soup with the 1/2 cup milk and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy red punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon size plastic container until all ingredients are dissolved.
Fill remainder of container with water to full line.
Freeze overnight.
Let thaw to slushy stage before serving.

title: broccoli - cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in just water until just tender.
In a heavy saucepot or slow cooker, combine soups, cheeses and 2, 3 or 4 cans water (water to personal preference consistency); heat on low to medium until cheese is completely melted.
Drain broccoli and add to soup and cheese.
Serve hot!!

title: sesame seed chicken
directions: Mix enough flour to cover chicken with salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons sesame seed in bowl.
In large baking dish, melt stick of margarine.
Dip chicken pieces in egg and milk, then in
flour mixture.
When all chicken is in baking dish, sprinkle
with sesame
seed.
Bake
at 350° until brown on bottom. Baste well until flour is covered.
Bake until browned well.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Thin cream cheese with a little milk and spread it on the pie shell.
Cover with layer of nicest berries (whole or halved if very large).
Mash remaining berries and cook with sugar and cornstarch until mixture is clear and thickened.
Let cool.
Pour over berries in pie shell.
Top with whipped cream (sweetened with small amount of sugar).
Chill several hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, baking powder and chopped nuts.
Add to first mixture.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: devil's fun cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured 8 X 8 pan.	Bake at 350 degrees until tester comes out clean.

title: pudding cake
directions: Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: traditional oatmeal cookies
directions: First, sift the flour and baking soda together.
Next blend vanilla, oil and sugars, then add the egg substitute.
Finally stir in the flour, oatmeal and nuts.
Preheat your oven to 350° and spray a cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop the dough onto the sheet with a teaspoon.
Bake for 8 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend cranberry sauce and 1 cup hot water until liquid; dissolve jello in other cup water.
Add 1 cup nuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture into square dish.
Put in freezer until set.
Spread the sour cream over it, then remaining cooled mixture.
A good salad and easy to make; pretty, too.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with foil or lid for first half hour.
Stir and cook, uncovered, for last half hour.

title: windex
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon jug and add water.

title: potato tots
directions: Put layer of potato tots in baking dish; add browned hamburger.
Top with celery and chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with pecans sausage stuffing
directions: Brown sausage (crumble).
Melt 1/3 cup butter over low heat. Add celery, green peppers and onion, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender.
Add 1/3 cup pecans, pepper and salt and cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sausage, bread cubes, egg and milk; set aside.
Place each chicken breast between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap or wax paper.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Place chicken breasts on flat surface.
Spoon sausage mixture in center of each chicken breast.
Combine 1 1/2 tablespoons melted butter, pecans and bread crumbs and pour on chicken breasts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sherbet delight
directions: Mix milk with Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add nuts. Crumble cookies and mix with Dream Whip and nuts.
Press half of this mixture on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan for crust.
Spread sherbet evenly over this.
Top with remainder of cookie mixture. Freeze several hours.
Serve in squares or slices.
Serves 12 or more.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Cream shortening, cream cheese and sugar well.
Beat in vanilla.
Gradually blend in flour.
Fill press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheets.
Hold press in semi-horizontal position and form wreaths by moving press in a circular motion.
Gently push ends of dough together to form wreaths.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove at once to cooling racks.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mom's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter or margarine, vanilla and sugars.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter, then sifted dry ingredients.
Form into tiny balls with the palms of your hands. Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with back of a fork to make crisscross.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Makes 50 to 60 small cookies.

title: heart-shaped cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cut bread into hearts with a 3-inch heart-shaped cookie cutter.
Thinly spread one heart shape with mayonnaise.
Arrange 2 or 3 slices of cucumber on top.
Sprinkle with Nature's Seasons salt.
Cover with another slice of bread.
Arrange on a plate to chill.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix next 5 ingredients, then nuts.
Pour into unbaked shell. Bake at 400° in oven for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Put quartered pickles in a jar with pepper, dill and garlic bulb.
Boil other ingredients; pour into jars and seal.
Do not overpack jars.

title: coal miner's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onions, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into ungreased deep dish pie plate. Mix 1 package of Jiffy cornbread mix; pour over mixture and bake until bread is done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together real well.
Place bread slices in pan.
Pour mixture over bread.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate overnight.
Fry in butter.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in one bowl.
Mix together the dry ingredients together in another bowl.
Slowly add dry ingredients to wet ingredients.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine ground beef, water and onions in large pot; mix well. Cook until ground beef is brown.
Add tomato paste, catsup and chili powder; mix well.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Yields 20 servings.

title: speedies
directions: Cut up your beef, pork or chicken.
Mix marinade sauce and put cut up meat in.
Can be marinated for 1 week.
Great for deer.

title: old timey lemonade
directions: Mix lemon juice, sugar and boiling water.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour mixture into a gallon jug.
Add cold water and throw in some of the lemon rinds.
Stir well.
Pour over ice in 10 to 12 ounce glasses.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate walnut sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, melt 1 cup butter; stir in 1/4 cup cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
In large mixer bowl, beat flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, cocoa mixture, 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until top is firm.
In saucepan, melt 1/4 cup butter with 1/4 cup cocoa and remaining sweetened condensed milk. Stir in confectioners sugar and walnuts; spread on warm cake.

title: bunny salad
directions: Place lettuce leaf on plate. Put 1/2 pear in center (body of bunny).
Add 2 raisins (for eyes), red cinnamon candy (for nose); 2 almonds (for ears); and a cottage cheese ball at large end (for tail).
Serve.

title: slim chickey
directions: Put chicken in a pan and pour Coke and ketchup over it. Add onion and bell pepper. Cook 40 minutes or until liquid cooks down and thickens. Put lid on and cook for 20 minutes.
Take lid off and finish cooking.

title: just great stuff
directions: Mix 1/2 cup water and salt together; simmer and stir for 2 minutes. Mix cornstarch and 1/4 cup water; take water off stove. Add cornstarch mixture and mix well. Roll "Great Stuff" with rolling pin between 2 pieces of wax paper. Cut shapes with knife or cookie cutter or model figures or jewelry. To keep dough firm and smooth as you work, wet your hands. Dough takes several days to dry!

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, toss hot spaghetti with olive oil.
In a small bowl, combine eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Stir into spaghetti.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 10-inch pie plate and form "crust".
Spread Ricotta over crust, but not to the edge.
Top with spaghetti sauce and spread out to the edge.
Bake, uncovered for 25 minutes.
Top with shredded Mozzarella.
Bake for 5 more minutes, until cheese melts.
Remove from oven, sprinkle with grated cheese and cool 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into wedges.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Combine salt, pepper and corn meal; dredge tomato slices.
Place in a heavy skillet of hot oil.
Fry slowly until brown, turning once.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter with confectioners sugar.
Mix in vanilla and water.
Put nuts in flour, then put nuts and flour into butter mixture.

title: denver filling
directions: Cook and stir 1/2 cup of minced onion and minced green pepper in butter or margarine until onion is tender.
Stir in diced ham; heat through.
Serve warm.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all together except onions.
Dip onions in mixture.
Put in hot deep fat a few rings at a time.
Fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: "no weep" meringue recipe
directions: Cook cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and water together until clear. Set aside. To the 3 egg whites, add a pinch of salt. Whip until foamy and standing in peaks. At this time, you add the cornstarch mixture to the egg whites. Continue beating until creamy. Gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar, beating until very creamy. Pile on pie and bake until golden brown.

title: coconut eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for the chocolate chips and the wax.
Form into small eggs.
Melt the chocolate chips and the wax together, then dip the small eggs into chocolate-wax mixture.
Let dry on wax paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Mix all ingredients in with cream cheese. Roll into ball, then roll into pecans and parsley. Chill.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Cut tofu into 1/4-inch cubes.
Shred bamboo shoots into thinner strips.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add mushrooms, tofu, bamboo shoots and chicken.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix soy sauce, sugar, salt, vinegar and pepper together and add to soup mixture.
Dissolve cornstarch in water and add to the pot while stirring to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Immediately stir in beaten eggs.
Add sesame oil and a few drops of Tabasco sauce (to taste).
You can freeze leftover mushrooms and bamboo shoots and liquid to cover in sandwich bag for later.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add and blend.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Decorate top with candies.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mom's bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and salt for 2 hours.
Drain.

title: orange carrots
directions: Cook carrots in 3/4 cup water.
Make sauce with remaining ingredients, stirring constantly.
Pour over carrots.

title: applesauce-oatmeal muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Mix next 5 ingredients and add alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Add last 3 ingredients.
Spoon into 12 well-buttered muffin cups.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and melted margarine.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and whipped topping and spread over pretzel layer. Dissolve gelatin in hot juice and add strawberries and juice to gelatin.
Let set partially, then spread on top of cream layer and chill thoroughly.

title: chew bread
directions: Stir together brown sugar and margarine, then add rest of ingredients.
Cook in a long flat pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix all together and cook in double boiler until thick.
Pour into a 9-inch cooked pie shell.
(I cook this in a microwave oven until thick, approximately 5 to 6 minutes.) Serves 8.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat until browned.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: In large bowl, break up 1 head of lettuce.
Put layer of peas, shredded carrots, onion and top with 1/2 jar mayonnaise.
Put on a layer of cheese and end with a topping of bacon bits.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: gumdrop batter bread
directions: Stir together 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, cinnamon and nutmeg. Heat milk, water, oil, sugar and salt over low heat until warm, stirring to blend.
Add liquid ingredients to flour-yeast mixture and beat until smooth, about 2 minutes on medium speed of mixer. Blend in eggs and gumdrops.
Stir in more flour to make stiff batter.
Beat batter until batter is elastic about 1 minute on medium speed.
Divide batter into 2 well-greased 1-quart baking dishes or molds.
Let rise in warm place until light bubbly.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool.

title: aunt doris' broccoli casserole
directions: Add water and melted butter to stuffing
and mix.
Add remaining ingredients and thoroughly mix together.
Bake uncovered in an ungreased 2 qt. casserole dish at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, butter, sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and salt. Then add bread.
Mix all together, then pour into a greased 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: herb tomato soup
directions: In a 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan or Dutch oven cook celery, leek and onion in heated oil until limp.
Mix in garlic, bouillon cubes, water, herbs and pepper, stirring until bouillon cubes dissolve.
Simmer, uncovered, until vegetables are just tender, 6 to 8 minutes.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes for two
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter over low heat, stir in flour and seasonings; cook over low heat, stirring until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk.
Heat to boiling stirring constantly.
In 1-quart casserole, layer half the potatoes, all the onion and half the sauce.
Top with remaining potatoes and sauce.
Dot with 1 teaspoon butter.
Cover and bake 30 minutes; uncover and bake until tender for 35 minutes.

title: poor boy
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Slice bread; spread with margarine.
Place cheese and tuna mix on bread.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Can be served open-face, presliced.
Top with American cheese.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat milk lukewarm.
Add sugar, salt and shortening to milk.
Add 1 cup flour and eggs; beat mixture well.
Add yeast mixture and stir well.
Add 3 cups flour and knead until dough doesn't stick to hands.
Place in greased bowl and let rise to top of bowl.
Form rolls and let rise to double size.
