Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Grease top of rolls while still hot.

title: brandy lace cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Lightly grease and flour cookie sheets. In a small saucepan, combine sugar, margarine, and corn syrup. Bring to boil over medium heat.
Stir in flour, pecans or walnuts, and brandy.
Drop 12 evenly spaced half teaspoonfuls of batter onto prepared cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes or until golden.
Cool 1-2 minutes or until cookies can be lifted but are still warm and pliable.
Remove with a spatula.
Curl around handle of a wooden spoon and slide off when crisp.
If cookies harden before curling, return to oven to soften.
Drizzle melted chocolate on top if desired.

title: maple mousse
directions: Mix the syrup with the egg yolks.
Cook in a double boiler until the mixture is slightly thick.
Let it cool.
When cool, fold the mixture into the whipped cream.
Place in freezer.
Just before it freezes, stir it thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: candied sweet potatoes(spicy)
directions: Drain potatoes; reserve liquid.
Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Place in 9 x 13-inch greased glass baking dish.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Stir margarine into 1 cup potato liquid.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Heat until margarine is melted and sugar is dissolved.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until syrup is thick.
Serves 6.

title: tuna-macaroni supper salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Combine mustard, mayo and dressing.
Add everything else.
Mix and chill well (approximately 4 hours). Garnish with hard-boiled egg, parsley, etc.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, flour, sugar and egg. Stir well, adding a little milk if needed. Drop into hot fat and fry until golden brown.

title: hot sweet pickles
directions: Buy good quality of pickles, not large pickles.
Many of the gallon jars of pickles are made from large cucumbers and they are soft and mushy.
Try to find the 48 ounce size.

title: old-time custard ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; gradually add milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs; return to hot mixture.
Cook 2 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.
Chill; stir in cream and vanilla.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.
Serve with toppings.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat, bell pepper and onion and drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, Crisco and cream cheese. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Alternate eggs and flour. Add lemon juice or almond flavoring and vanilla. Bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours (start in a cold oven). Glaze while hot after turning out of pan. This makes a large cake so use a large tube pan.

title: angel buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water in medium bowl.
Mix in Bisquick and milk until dough forms.
Gently smooth into ball on surface dusted with baking mix.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch biscuits cutters dipped in baking mix. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let rise about 30 minutes or until soft and puffed.
Heat oven to 425°.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes until golden brown.

title: flounder parmesan
directions: Place fish on pan.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs, cheese and spices.
Wet this with oil and juice.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Boil 3 to 5 minutes until brown.

title: cider-glazed baked ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place ham in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Pour apple cider over ham.
In a medium bowl, stir together remaining ingredients, except apple slices.
Spoon sauce over entire ham. Bake, basting every 15 minutes with pan juices, for 60 to 70 minutes until heated through.
Serve with pan juices and garnish with apple slices.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs together until light colored and creamy; add nutmeg. Mix sugar and flour.
Pour milk over flour mixture; beat well. Add eggs and butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 350°.
Bake for about 30 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll batter into little balls and bake on 350° for 8 minutes. Take out of oven and put Hershey's Kisses in centers and bake for 2 minutes.

title: *quick potatoes and mushrooms in sour cream
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms. Saute until tender.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and hot pepper seasoning.
Cook over medium heat, stirring carefully with pancake turner, about 5 minutes, or until potatoes are heated.
Stir in sour cream with the dill and serve.
Serves 4.

title: english apple pie
directions: Mix butter and brown sugar.
Stir in flour, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and water until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Mound apples in pie pan. Mix sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Spoon pecan mixture over apples.
Bake on lower rack at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: company coffee cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together except sugar, cinnamon and nuts until well blended.
In small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Layer in greased 9 x 13-inch pan: half batter and half sugar mixture; repeat.
Swirl.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm or cool.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Pour 1 stick melted butter over graham cracker crumbs and blend.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello, Kool-Aid and hot water.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Add enough water to mixture to make a gallon. Put in milk cartons and freeze.
Thaw one out completely, let other melt slightly and crush.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Brown onion and beef and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add rice.
Stir in cheese.
In greased casserole dish, layer cabbage and meat mixture and repeat.
Combine tomato sauce and water.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crisp cookies
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in order. Add the salt, cream of tartar, soda and flour which have been mixed together.
Fold in the Rice Krispies, oatmeal, coconut and chopped nuts.
Form dough into little balls and put on cookie sheet.
Press down. Bake 10 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage.
Mix in chicken and sesame seeds, onion and almonds.
Mix in separate bowl oil, sugar, vinegar, pepper, salt and packages of chicken broth from Ramen noodles.
Mix into cabbage.
Just before serving, break up noodles and mix in cabbage.

title: sauteed mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rest of ingredients.
Add mushrooms and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chinese rice casserole
directions: Saute the onion, celery and green pepper in butter.
Boil water.
Add soup mix and stir.
Add rice and stir.
Combine rest of ingredients.
Bake in a covered 9 x 12-inch casserole dish about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: delores' zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in oil and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients together and add zucchini and nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: chili
directions: Soften garlic in water.
Add oil and saute 1 to 2 minutes. Add hamburger and cook until meat browns slightly.
Add chili powder, salt, cumin seed, tomatoes and beans.
Start boiling, stirring often, 25 minutes.
Add tomato paste and sugar.
Let simmer 15 minutes.

title: cabbage rolls(sarma)
directions: Blanch cabbage in hot water to separate leaves; drain.
Mix together pork, beef, rice and grated cheese and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Make into balls and roll into cabbage leaves.
Spread 1/2 of sauerkraut in bottom of 8-quart pan. Arrange cabbage rolls on top.
Put remaining sauerkraut on top. Cover with water.
Bring to a boil and then simmer for about 4 hours.

title: walnut crisps
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into large bowl.
Mix in thoroughly with fork:
shortening, egg yolk, milk and vanilla.
Form into balls, size of small walnuts.
Place on cookie sheet.
Press 1/16 inch thick with bottom of greased glass dipped in sugar.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts. Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until slightly brown at 375°.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: orange-coconut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Sift flour; measure and sift with sugar, baking powder and salt onto wax paper.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter and rind until smooth; add flour mixture and milk.
Mix for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and beat for 2 more minutes.
Stir in coconut. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: super-special ham loaf
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
Put in bottom of loaf pan.
Cut slices of pineapple and arrange on bottom of pan. Combine ham, pork, eggs, milk, crackers and potato chips.
Pack into pan, being careful not to disarrange pineapple.
Bake at 375° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Unmold and serve.

title: ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Finely dice ham and onion in 2-quart bowl. Add cheese, egg and salt and pepper. Mix well. Spray mini muffin pan with Pam. Unroll crescent rolls and press into one large rectangle. With pizza cutter, cut dough into 24 pieces. Press dough into mini muffin cup. Fill with ham mixture. Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: molly's summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain well and mash with fork.
Add other vegetables, soup, sour cream.
Mix stuffing mix with oleo.
Put some stuffing mix in bottom of a baking dish. Add squash mixture and rest of stuffing mix.
Bake uncovered 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coca-cola chicken
directions: Put in pot and cook on low heat until chicken is done.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts and parsley).
Season to taste.
Roll in ball in wax paper.
Chill.
Roll in combined nuts and parsley.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate raspberry brownie torte
directions: In top of double boiler, set over barely simmering water, melt the unsweetened chocolate with the butter, stirring until smooth.

title: fresh apple crunch cake
directions: Sift together the flour, spices and soda.
Mix oil, eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add apples, brandy, nuts and vanilla; mix well. Mixture will be stiff.
Spread in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Rich cake; do not frost. Crust is crunchy like cookie.
Inside is moist and chewy.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except grated cheeses with wooden spoon.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Grate Jack and Cheddar cheese and spread on top.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: brownie pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, flour and cocoa and mix well. Beat eggs with vanilla.
Add to first mixture, cooking until it thickens.
Pour into pie shell and cook 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven or until it tests done.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: oven fried okra
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut okra into 1/2-inch slices.
Mix together bread crumbs and seasoning. Dip okra in salad dressing and roll in bread crumbs.
Liberally coat a nonstick cookie sheet with cooking spray.
Place okra on sheet and bake for 15 minutes. Turn okra over and bake 15 minutes more.

title: cheesed carrots
directions: Boil carrots until tender; drain.
Place carrots in greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
In saucepan, melt cheese and margarine, stirring constantly.
Pour over drained carrots.
Top with cornflake crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly or about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle wafer crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook over medium heat until it reaches the hard crack stage. Watch it carefully toward the end so it doesn't burn.
Pour over popped corn.
Stir.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain well.
Add 2 cans tomato sauce and Italian seasoning.
Simmer meat mixture while cooking lasagna noodles.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drain noodles when tender, then layer 3 to 4 noodles on bottom of pan. Spread half of meat and tomato sauce mixture on noodles, then half of sliced Mozzarella and half of sliced Cheddar.
Make second layer with remaining noodles, meat, Mozzarella and Cheddar.
Bake uncovered for 25 minutes, then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper.
Drain and add meat to 3 cans of beans.
Mix 2 cups ketchup and brown sugar together.
In oblong pan put bean mixture and top with sauce and brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir mixture and then bake 30 minutes more.

title: honey clusters (strufoli)
directions: Set out a deep saucepan or automatic deep fryer for deep frying and heat fat or oil to 365°.
Meanwhile, place flour and salt into a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of the flour. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing slightly after each addition.
Add vanilla extract.
Mix well to make a soft dough.

title: talia's chocolate truffles
directions: Chop the chocolate. Combine the chocolate and cream in a saucepan over low heat. Stir constantly until the cream boils. Remove from the heat and stir until the chocolate melts. Pour into a bowl. Press plastic wrap directly on the surface of the chocolate to prevent the formation of a skin and refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours. Or if you're in a hurry, freeze 1/2 hour. Shape the mixture into 1-inch balls. Roll the balls in cocoa. Makes 16 servings.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Slice onions into rings and soak in milk for 1 hour.
Mix ingredients.
Dip rings into mixture and fry until golden brown.

title: pizza dough
directions: Put yeast and warm water together; add salt, honey, olive oil and the yeast and warm water together.
Mix flour and salt to the mixture.
Let rise for 1 hour, then work out on pizza pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice to make 2 cups of cooked rice.
Place all ingredients in casserole dish.
Stir well.
Sprinkle potato chips on top for crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: birds eye golden glow
directions: Cut bacon in 1-inch pieces and fry until crisp. Remove bacon; saute onion in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat until delicately browned. Add frozen corn; cover and cook until corn is thawed, stirring occasionally. Cook 5 minutes longer. Add parsley and seasonings; serve with bacon sprinkled over top.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together jello, water and sugar.
Grind cranberries, apple, oranges and orange peeling.
Mix all ingredients together; pour into bowl or pan.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: skillet corn
directions: Lightly fry beef and onion in butter.
Stir in flour.
Add milk.
Cook until thickened.
Add corn.
Add cheese and bell pepper.
Serve on buttered toast.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a medium bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bar
directions: Melt chips and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half of mixture in greased pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in milk, vanilla and egg.
Pour into pan.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° (325° if you use a glass pan).
Toothpick should come out clean.
Chill before serving.

title: church brunch special
directions: Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Add sausage, cheese and bread; stir.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set in refrigerator for 12 hours.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cover with foil for 1/2 of baking time only.

title: frito salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and let set overnight in refrigerator or several hours. When ready to serve, mix with:

title: chicken 'n vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to package directions.
Broiler cooked with 1 1/2 tsp. salt, boned and coarsely chopped.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°; cool.

title: lockhart lemon ice box pie
directions: In a bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine. Press mixture in bottom and up sides of pie plate to form crust. Set aside.

title: mushrooms stuffed with crabmeat, cheese and chives
directions: Toss mushrooms with lemon juice in a bowl.
Combine oil, vinegar, onion, garlic, sugar and dressing mix.
Pour over mushrooms and toss again.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Toss occasionally.
Drain and serve.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, yeast, buttermilk, water and margarine in saucepan until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Slowly add to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Stir in cheese and enough flour to make a stiff dough. Place in greased bake sheet.
Knead 7 to 10 minutes.
Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, 1 hour or more.
Mix egg and milk; brush over loaves.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: garlic and cheese biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl except butter. Drop in pan by spoon.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Take out of oven and melt 1/2 cup of butter in saucepan.
Add garlic to taste.
Brush on top of biscuits.

title: casserole of some sort
directions: Mix butter, flour, salt and milk (add slowly).
Let sauce cook for a few minutes.
Add 1 1/4 cups diced cooked chicken or turkey. Add to sauce 1 cup drained peas and pimento.
Grease casserole dish.
Place Doritos corn chips on bottom layer, then put sauce over the chips.
Place extra chips on top.
Place cheese over top. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 25 minutes.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix together and beat for 2 minutes.
Place pudding layer over cheese layer.
Let sit up for several more hours or overnight. Then take leftover Cool Whip and spread over pudding.
If you like, you can sprinkle chopped nuts over top.

title: plain pizza bread
directions: Thaw frozen unbaked bread in microwave.
Spread on greased and floured pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Spread to 1/2-inch of edge. Spread 4 to 6 cloves garlic steeped in 3 tablespoons of olive oil. Top with Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In plastic bag or bowl, shake all ingredients until vegetables are coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake, stirring once 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Put lemon juice on top.
Combine sour cream, soup, mayonnaise and wine.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: sour cream twists
directions: Boil sour cream and remove from heat.
Add baking soda, butter, salt and sugar.
Let cool. Add yeast and warm water mixture, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add flour.
Let rise.
Roll out like cinnamon rolls. Spread with butter and sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold in half.
Cut into strips and twist.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until lightly browned. Drizzle with powdered sugar and milk frosting while hot.

title: cream vegetable soup
directions: Chop vegetables finely. Cook slowly for 1 hour in 1 pint of water boiling. Add butter and flour. Blend together. Add 2 cups milk; bring to a boil. Serve with cheese and crackers.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix for 10 minutes at medium speed.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Put about 1/2 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan or mix in batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: plastic pickles
directions: Step 1:
Place cucumber slices in a stone or glass jar. Cover with lime dissolved in 1
or
quarts cold water.
Let stand 12 hours.
Drain and
wash
in
cold water.
Slices must always be completely covered in
each step.
Add a little more or less water, as needed.

title: egg rolls
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add pork chops.
Add onions, bell peppers, carrots, mushrooms and bamboo shoots.
Cook down, adding soy sauce and cabbage (stop adding cabbage when you feel it is enough).
Take off stove and add bean sprouts while still hot. Wrap in wrappers and deep fry until brown.

title: heart safe fried fillets
directions: Cut fillets into bite sized pieces.
Dip into egg white which has been beaten with the water, then dip into bread crumbs.
Fry in small amount of canola oil in skillet until golden brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Then turn down to 350° and bake another 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together with a spoon (do not use mixer).
Batter will be stiff.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chef salad sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well; keep refrigerated.

title: chili americain
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in a little margarine; set aside. In same pan, brown ground beef, drain.
Add all ingredients except kidney beans to a large pot.
Slice the tomatoes as they are added to the pot.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce to simmer and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Stir in beans with some liquid and reheat until bubbly.
Serve with grated cheese on top.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all together.
Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Pour mixture in crock-pot.
Cook 3 hours on low.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in 2 cups water about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir until soup is hot and thick.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup, water and nuts until a light brown.
Take off fire and add soda; stir.
Pour into greased pan.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add corn, peas and mushroom and chicken soup. Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 buttered 2-quart casserole dishes.
Top one with crumbled cornbread and dot with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dr. taylor's father's brunswick stew
directions: Put all meats and onions on about 9:00 A.M. in enough water to cover.
Boil good, until meat leaves bones of chicken, then take out all meat with strainer and get bones out, then put back in water.
Add butter beans, tomatoes and 1/4 cup of crushed red pepper.
Boil until around 4 or 5 o'clock.
Cream potatoes in house and add to stew along with corn, 1/2 cup salt, a little black pepper and 1 cup sugar.
Add 2 pounds butter, tomato paste and catsup.
If not enough salt, add to taste.
Keep stirring to keep from sticking.
Cook in large iron pot.

title: pork pepper steak
directions: Combine pineapple juice and water to soya sauce, cornstarch, chicken base, pepper and garlic.
Heat oil in large skillet. Stir-fry pork and green peppers 3 to 4 minutes, until brown.
Push meat to one side of pan.
Add liquid and pineapple.
Stir and cook to thicken.
Pour this recipe over cooked rice.

title: a different mix
directions: In a large bowl, mix cereal, pretzels, nuts and crackers. Drizzle oil over mixture.
In another bowl, mix dressing mix and dill weed and sprinkle over cereal mixture.
Place in grocery bag and shake well.
Allow mixture to sit in bag about 2 hours, shaking periodically.
Ready to serve.

title: boston baked corn
directions: Combine catsup, onion, brown sugar, dry mustard and salt in 1-quart casserole bowl.
Stir in drained corn.
Top with diced bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Garnish with additional cooked bacon, if desired.

title: chicken in sauce
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Season with salt, pepper and flour.
In large skillet, brown chicken; do not cook.
In saucepan, mix tomatoes, onion, pepper, parsley, tomato sauce and seasonings. Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes on low, until sauce thickens.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until done and tender.

title: paella style vegetables
directions: In a pan with a little water, saute zucchini, peppers, onion and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes and their juice, salt, pepper, broth, rice and lemon juice.
Bring to a rolling boil. Pour into large casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 12 minutes. Stir in broccoli, peas and Parmesan.
Make 6 depressions in the rice mixture with a spoon.
Break a raw egg into each depression. Sprinkle with salt.
Cover and bake another 18 to 20 minutes.

title: candied yams with apple and banana
directions: Melt the fat in a large skillet. Stir in apple and orange juices, salt and spices. Add the yams. Bring to a boil. Cover, lower the heat and simmer for 10 minutes (or until yams are just tender). Add apples and bananas and simmer for an additional 2 minutes.
Serve with chopped roasted peanuts. Yield:
4 portions.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Stir raw vegetables into soups; add some water.
Add other ingredients.
Heat in microwave or oven until warm.

title: date candy
directions: Cook the sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Add the cut up dates.
Cook again to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts, vanilla and margarine.
Beat well and pour into buttered pans.

title: beef porcupine meat balls
directions: Mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings; form into small balls. Cook in hot oil until light brown.
Add tomato sauce and water. Mix well; cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: champagne cocktail
directions: Sprinkle sugar cubes with mandarin juice, let dry.
In each champagne glass, place 1 mandarin sugar cube and 1 mandarin section.
Fill glass with very cold champagne.
Sugar cube dissolves very slowly and lasts through 2 or 3 refills!

title: no bake whiskey balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into little balls (the size of an olive).
Roll in extra confectioners sugar.
Keep in a cool place.

title: lye soap
directions: Note:
You
will need a wooden spoon, a lined cardboard box, rubber
gloves,
a	thermometer
and
1 blanket for this recipe. Use stainless steel or granite containers only.

title: asparagus lunch
directions: Wash asparagus.
Cut off the hard ends.
Cut into quarter-inch pieces.
In a skillet, combine asparagus pieces, chopped onion and oil.
Simmer until not quite done.
Break eggs on the mixture and mix all.
Cook as you would scrambled eggs.

title: miss florence's cake(served at brownsville for tea)
directions: Add alternating wet and dry ingredients to butter and sugar mixture and egg yolks.
Beat well when all ingredients are mixed. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Bake in tube pan, buttered well to make a large delectable cake.

title: pizza bake
directions: Microwave potatoes and onions 5 minutes.
Stir; microwave 5 more minutes.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Pour over potatoes and onions.
Add Cheddar cheese soup and then spaghetti sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; sprinkle cheese and then bake until it melts.

title: cowboy caviar
directions: Mix the first 10 ingredients and cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Fill bottom with apples, sliced thin. Combine cornstarch, cinnamon, salt, sugar, melted margarine and syrup.
Pour over apples.
Cover with top crust.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes until crust is brown and apples are tender.
Remove from oven.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil chicken
in 4 cups water with celery tops, sliced onion, salt and pepper until meat is done.
When cool, remove meat from bone.
Reserve stock and skim fat when cool.
Saute bacon, pepper, onion and celery until transparent.
Add parsley, tomatoes, chicken stock, water and shrimp boil.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken and okra; cook 10 to 20 minutes more.
May be served over rice or as a soup.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: onion casserole bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, onion, salt and yeast.
Stir water and margarine into dry mixture, beat by hand 30 seconds.
Mix in only enough reserved flour to make very thick batter.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. With floured hands, smooth top of dough in casserole.
Fill large pan with hot tap water 1-inch deep.
Place casserole in water. Cover, let rise 25 minutes.
Break beaten egg on loaf.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until done.
Loosen bread from casserole, using flexible spatula.
Remove and cool on wire rack.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Saute onion (chopped finely) in water and butter.
Add flour, mushroom soup, cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, mushrooms, parsley and buttered beef.
Pour into pie plate.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and paprika on top.
Bake until hot.
Serve with crackers (suggest Town House).

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place half of bread cubes in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer cream cheese chunks over bread. Then layer with meat.
Put remaining bread cubes on top.
Mix together eggs, milk and maple syrup.
Pour over casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and let set overnight.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix first five ingredients together; roll into a ball or log. Then roll in chili mix.
Chill and slice.
Serve with crackers.

title: homemade wine
directions: A good many husbands are certainly spoiled in the process of cooking and are not so tender and good.
Some women go about it as if their husbands were bladders and blow them up.
Others let them freeze by their indifference.
Some keep them in a stew by irritating ways and words.
Others roast them.
Some keep them in a pickle all their lives.

title: orange smoothie
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Blend for 3 -4 minutes

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and jam.
Mix together flour and spices.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk and orange juice.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil skinned chicken until done.
Reserve broth for noodles to be boiled in.
Pull chicken from bone and chop into small pieces while noodles are boiling.
Put cubed chicken, soup and Ro-Tel into casserole dish.
Mix well.
Add desired amount of noodles and top with cubes of Velveeta cheese.
Bake in 350° oven until cheese is melted and casserole is bubbling.

title: refrigerator cheese bread
directions: Combine 3 cups
flour,
yeast,
sugar and salt in large bowl. Heat milk and 2 cups water in saucepan until very warm. Add to dry ingredients
gradually.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add 1 cup flour and beat at high speed for
2 minutes.
Stir in cheese and enough flour to make a soft dough.

title: texas style beans and rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients (except cheese and chips).
Bake in covered casserole in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese and then corn chips.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes more.
(To retain whole appearance of beans, add about 30 minutes into the baking time.)

title: cheese and macaroni
directions: Mix together all but margarine.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Dot butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: onion cauliflower bake
directions: Melt butter; add onions and saute.
Add flour and salt; stir and add milk (portions to make cream sauce).
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Then add cauliflower and parsley.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with onions.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli to thaw.
Mix together other ingredients.
Drain broccoli.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pete's prize
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk.
Add pie filling and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
May be stored in refrigerator or freezer.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and stir well.
Cover and cook on high setting for 4 to 6 hours.
Serves 8.
Serve with corn bread muffins.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In saucepan blend the first 4 indredients.
Boil 1-2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix together and drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: special pecan pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Beat in sugar and baking powder.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and pecans; mix well.
Pour into a greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: If desired, nuts and raisins can be added if baked as loaf bread.

title: jello dessert
directions: Prepare the 2 packages cherry jello as directed.
Chill in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix 1 package lemon jello, 1 cup hot water, the cream cheese, marshmallows, Dream Whip and pineapple.
Pour over jellied cherry jello.
Chill.

title: m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugar for 2 minutes.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in M&M's.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool for about 10 minutes.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Cook at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: "jim bane" sauce
directions: Place ingredients in blender and do at low speed for 1 minute or two until sauce is smooth and chutney is well-blended.
Serve on shrimp and other fish or with cheese and crackers on a side dish.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain liquid from salmon into measuring cup.
Add milk to make 1 cup liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan, add onions and cook until tender but not brown.
Blend in flour, salt, and Tabasco.
Add milk mixture and cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Flake salmon and add to sauce with lemon juice.
Stir in 1/2 cup cornflake crumbs.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Divide into 8-10 portions and shape into cones.
Roll in remaining cornflake crumbs to coat well.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake in hot oven 400 degrees for 20-25 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with tabasco and tartar sauce.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Cook noodles according to directions.
Beat eggs and sugar together. Mix cheese, milk and margarine and add egg mixture.
Mix all ingredients with cooked noodles. Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan (I prefer glass).
Top with sugar and cinnamon or cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in broiler pan. Combine other ingredients and pour over chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1-1/2 hour.

title: frankfruit pudding
directions: Peel and core apples and cut into slices. Sprinkle with lemon juice to prevent discoloration.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Toast the bread slices in a moderate oven at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes until they are lightly browned and very dry.
Rub through a coarse strainer or grind in a blender.
Add enough apple juice to the crumbs to moisten them thoroughly.
Put half of the bread mixture in a greased baking dish.
Spoon over the apple slices and sprinkle with raisins.
Cover with the remaining bread mixture. Bake at 375°
for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve warm with cream.

title: louisiana shrimp gumbo
directions: Peel shrimp, uncooked, and devein.
Make roux (dark) of flour and oil.
Add shrimp to this for a few minutes, stirring constantly.
Set aside.
Smother okra and onions in oil.
Add tomatoes when okra is nearly cooked.
Then add water, bay leaf, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add shrimp and roux to this; cover and slowly cook for 30 minutes.
Serve in bowl over a little rice. Hot French bread completes the meal.
Servings:
6 to 8.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and marinate.

title: peanut pattie(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and corn syrup in a 2 quart microwave-safe glass bowl.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Add peanuts and stir.
Cook 7 to 9 minutes more.
Add butter, vanilla and red food coloring.
Beat with spoon until dull red.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper.

title: ga ga's chocolate chip cookies(these are the best!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
(I sift the dry ingredients 3 times together and just put it on waxed paper.)
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine Crisco, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract; beat until creamy. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture, then stir in Nestle morsels and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
(If you want large cookies, then use a larger spoonful.) Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.
Put on brown paper to cool.
(I use large brown paper bags torn open.)

title: mary lucci's easter bread
directions: Mix to bread texture.
Knead; let raise more than double. Knead again, then shape into braid, ring, round or bread size. Let raise.
Bake in low temperature oven (325°).
Let brown on top and bottom.
Easy to burn.

title: herbed italian skillet bread
directions: In a medium bowl, dissolve the sugar in 1/2 cup of the water. Sprinkle with yeast on top; set aside until it starts to foam, about 5 minutes.

title: horace's veritable venison
directions: Boil venison until it flakes off the bone.
Chop meat into fine pieces.
Place in baking pan.
Mix sauce ingredients.
Baste meat often during baking process.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°.

title: chocolate crispies]
directions: Stir until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Save drippings.
Place on bacon on paper towel to drain.
Slice cabbage and place in bacon drippings. Salt to taste.
Cover and cook over medium heat stirring often. Cook until tender.
Top with crumbled bacon.
Serve hot.

title: crunchy rice salad
directions: Cook rice, omitting salt.
Cool.
Combine rice and next 5 ingredients.
Combine vinegar, oil and soy sauce.
Pour over rice mixture.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: garlic dip
directions: Combine the ingredients except vegetables. Chill, then serve.

title: southern chicken and dumplings
directions: In a
large
mixing
bowl, combine 2 cups of flour with buttermilk and shortening. Mix well.
Gradually add more flour until it forms a very firm dough.
Roll out on floured surface to about 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch wide strips.

title: shelly's mexican casserole(microwave dish)
directions: Cook ground beef 5 minutes on High and crumble.
Mix soup and tomatoes.
Layer in a 2-quart casserole half of tortilla chips, beef, onion and soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cook uncovered at 155° using a temperature probe or about 12 to 14 minutes (until cheese melts, heated through) on Medium-high.

title: squash supreme casserole
directions: In a large 3-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients, except herb stuffing.
Sprinkle stuffing mix on top; dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: apple-candy bar salad
directions: Chop Snickers.
Chop apples.
Mix with Cool Whip.
Top with chocolate curls and/or peanuts.

title: chili-n-cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Spread cut side of each English muffin with 1 teaspoon butter and place, buttered side down, in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage in a skillet until browned, stirring to crumble; drain.
Layer half each of sausage, chiles and cheese over English muffins.
Combine sour cream and eggs; pour over casserole.
Repeat layers with remaining sausage, chiles and cheese; cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: country rib-vegetable dinner
directions: Put ribs into a large bowl.
Dredge with flour to coat all sides well.
Reserve extra flour.
Heat oil in a heavy, ovenproof Dutch oven or casserole.
Brown meat on all sides over medium heat. Sprinkle with reserved flour.
Add apple cider, salt and pepper. Heat to boiling, stirring juices to blend in flour.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Skim fat if excessive.
Add cabbage. Cover, bake 30 minutes longer or until vegetables and meat are tender.

title: cheese balls
directions: Soften cream cheese and Cheddar cheese in microwave.
Add onions, green peppers, olives, mayonnaise, lemon juice and hot sauce.
Mix together very well.
Separate into 2 balls, roll in pecans, then chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add soup and onion; mix well in 2-quart casserole.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix.
Pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered. Enjoy!

title: broccoli with pimiento cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Arrange in shallow, buttered 1 1/4-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup, butter, lemon juice and cheese.
Spoon over broccoli.
Top with crackers, almonds and pimiento.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and roll in pecans.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Add ingredients (in order) to a 9 x 11-inch pan (layer by layer).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or to a light golden brown.
Cool; cut into squares and enjoy.

title: porkepine meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomatoes.
Shape into meat balls; cover with 1 quart of tomatoes and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350° in oven.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, toss together the graham cracker crumbs and the 1/2 cup melted butter.
Press mixture into the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine until transparent.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and
chili
powder to onion in frying pan and heat. In bottom of	9
x
13-inch
pan,
put yellow hominy, drained. Pour cheese mixture
over top.	Top with Fritos.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain and rinse.
Put meat in an oblong pan. Layer onions, potatoes, carrots and cabbage on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° until potatoes and carrots are done.
You may leave cabbage out of recipe!

title: cheese in a blanket
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Unroll crescent dough and pinch together seams.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Place cream cheese in middle and enclose dough around.
Brush over with egg yolk. Sprinkle with more dill weed.
Bake in oven as directed on crescent roll package.
Garnish with apples and grapes.
Serve with crackers.

title: berry good banana smoothie
directions: You will need a blender.

title: whole wheat chips and coffee bars
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
In large bowl beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually add brown sugar, oil and vanilla; beat well.
Dissolve coffee crystals in cold water, gradually stir into egg mixture.
Add dry ingredients; beat until well combined.
Pour batter into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate bits and nuts evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Drizzle Coffee Glaze.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, Bisquick, egg, butter, sugar and milk. Pour 1/2 of batter into greased casserole. Layer 1 can green chilies on top, then 1 package Monterey Jack cheese. Pour remaining batter and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: quick tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini to package directions; let cool.
Combine all ingredients until everything is well blended with dressing.
Let cool in the refrigerator (approximately 1 hour).

title: strawberry delight(8 servings)
directions: Wash, hull and slice strawberries.
Cut cake into bite size pieces.
Whip the cream.
Combine in large bowl dry pudding mix, sour cream, milk and orange peel.
Mix on low speed 1 to 2 minutes or until thick and well blended.
Fold in whipped cream.
Layer in large serving bowl as follows:
1/2 of cake pieces, 1/3 of the strawberries and 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Repeat layers.
Arrange remaining strawberries over top.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Thaw frozen broccoli.
Lay cooked chicken in the bottom of a casserole.
Lay broccoli on top of the chicken.
Mix the soup and mayonnaise; pour it over the broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sloppy joe pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef and drain.
Add Manwich and mix.
Spread on crust; top with mushrooms and cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes; cut into wedges and serve.
Any toppings can be added to this recipe.

title: one dish lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add sauce, water and sugar. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 sauce mixture, half uncooked noodles, 1/2 cottage cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with 1/3 Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Combine 1 cup Mozzarella with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese and sprinkle on top.
Cover with foil.
Best when refrigerated overnight, but can be baked right away at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pull thawed bread into walnut size pieces.
Fill pan with a single layer. Heat together other ingredients and pour over dough; let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; invert to serve.

title: hazelnut-strawberry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour 9 inch square baking pan.

title: oyster snacks
directions: Empty oyster crackers into bowl.
Pour on oil and stir to moisten all crackers.
Add Ranch dressing pack and dill weed. stir until all crackers are coated.

title: working for peanuts pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon mixture into pie crust and sprinkle with peanuts. Chill 8 hours. Makes 1 pie.

title: strawberry watermelon slush
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice cubes in blender.
Blend well.
Gradually add ice.
Blend until smooth.
Serve immediately. Garnish with cube of watermelon or strawberry.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Combine bulgur and stock in a big bowl until liquid is absorbed (1 hour).
Add corn, bell pepper, carrots, onions, cheese and egg and mix.
Then add tomato sauce and all spices and stir again.
Wash and trim squash as needed and cut in half lengthwise. Scoop out seeds and some pulp from each half.
Mix in any pulp (hot seeds) with bulgur mix.
Stuff and mound onto each squash half.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes in pan filled with 1/4-inch water.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture after each addition.
Combine flour and soda and add to cream mixture alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix well and stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and
floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour or so until toothpick comes out clean.

title: microwave pecans
directions: In a 3-quart casserole microwave butter on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Blend sauces into butter.
Add pecans and stir to coat well.
Microwave on High 7 to 11 minutes or until pecans are cooked.
Drain off any remaining butter.
Turn pecans out onto paper towel.
Store in airtight container.

title: biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Sift together next 6 ingredients. Add yeast to sour milk; refrigerate.
Do not let rise.
Can be kept at least 1 week.
Drop by spoonful into a greased pan, touching sides.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Mix and form into balls.
Press hole with thumb and put olive in ball.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze until firm.
Bake frozen 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix first four ingredients and let stand in ice water for 3 hours.
Bring remaining ingredients to boil with the cucumbers. Put in jars and seal.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and salt with an electric mixer.
Stir in chocolate chips; set aside.
In another bowl combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, cocoa, baking soda, salt and water.
Next, mix oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Fill cupcake papers 1/2 full with cocoa batter.
Place 1 teaspoonful cream cheese mixture in center of each cupcake and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
No frosting is needed.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well
Add vinegar and food coloring; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Best if made in 4 layers.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening, sugar, egg, flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in alternately with milk.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes.
Immediately roll in butter, 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.

title: layered danish green salad
directions: Layer above ingredients in order listed in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Combine with soups, broth, green chilies and sour cream.
Add deboned chicken.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer half of the tortillas, then half of the chicken mixture, then cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Reserve 1/4 cup to flour blueberries. Add the remainder alternately with milk to the first mixture. Beat thoroughly.
Stir in berries.
Pour into a greased shallow pan and bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve hot.

title: pepper bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into hot cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown and crusty.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake into
2 layers.
When cool, slice each layer, making 4 layers.
Mix coconut, sour cream and sugar.
Save 1/2 cup of mixture.
Spread rest between cake layers.
Mix 1/2 cup coconut mixture with
9 ounces Cool Whip.
Cover top and sides of cake. Refrigerate
for
at
least
days before serving. Will stay good 2 or 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: howard's pizza sans tomato
directions: Sauce:
Combine mayo, Parmesan and spices.
Spread on pizza crust.
Add other ingredients.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: texas taters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a well-greased baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: fast-fixin' chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour oil into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Tilt pan until bottom is covered with oil.
Put remaining ingredients into pan. Stir with fork or spoon until blended. Scrape sides and spread batter evenly in pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cooled cake may be sprinkled with powdered sugar or iced as desired.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Drain mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Combine all ingredients and let chill for at least 2 hours prior to serving.

title: burger delight
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in oil.
Add other ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add grated cheese. Let melt.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: shrimp delights
directions: Heat all vegetables and bay leaves in vegetable oil and margarine until tender.
Then add shrimp which has been peeled, deveined and cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: barbara bush's zucchini soup
directions: Chop unpeeled zucchini, shallots and garlic.
Put in heavy frying pan.
Cook with butter for 10 to 20 minutes.
Stir to keep from burning.
You don't want it to brown.
Put all ingredients and seasoning in blender and blend.
Add cream.
Serve hot with croutons.
Serve cold with chives.
Makes 8 serving and is also suitable for freezing.

title: spinach stuffed flank steak
directions: In a small bowl soak dried tomatoes in enough hot water to cover for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Snip into small pieces.
Meanwhile, score meat by making shallow diagonal cuts at 1 inch intervals in diamond pattern on both sides.
Place meat between two pieces of plastic wrap.
Working from center to edges, pound with flat side of meat mallet into 12 x 8 inch rectangle.
Remove plastic wrap. Sprinkle with the salt and pepper.
Spread the spinach over the steak.
Sprinkle with the softened tomatoes, parmesan cheese, and basil.
Roll the steak up from the short side.
Secure with wooden toothpicks at 1 inch intervals, starting 1/2 inch from 1 end.
Cut between toothpicks into eight 1-inch thick slices.
Place slices, cut side down, on unheated rack of broiler pan.
Broil 3-4 inches from the heat to desired doneness, turning once.
(Allow 10-12 minutes for medium-rare or 12-16 minutes for medium.)
Before serving remove the toothpicks.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the rice evenly in the bottom of the pan.
Heat the soups and milk in a saucepan.
Pour the soups over the rice and stir.
Lay the chicken pieces over the top.
Sprinkle the onion soup mix over the chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all and chill.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Batter will be very thick.
Bake in tube pan at 350° approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar and eggs together.
Add melted butter. Mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
In separate bowl mix flour, soda and salt.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Roll dough into log.
Put in refrigerator.
Slice into 1/4-inch pieces and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: mama's apple custard
directions: Mix
all ingredients well.
Pour
into	2
pie	shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: miss nellie's chilli
directions: Brown hamburger.
Pour off grease.
Add all other ingredients. Cook slowly for at least 1 hour.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: In large pot, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid; set both aside.
In same pot, saute onion in butter until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened.
Gently stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved cooking liquid until soup is desired consistency. I always use more carrots and less celery (depending on your taste).
Yields about 2 1/2 quarts; makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy banana peanut shake
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender on medium for 40 to 45 seconds.
Serve cold in small glasses, 3/4 cup each.
Serves 4.

title: winter corn chowder(modern)
directions: Rinse corn and combine with broth in saucepan; bring to boil. Remove to heat and allow to stand for 2 hours, then cook for 45 minutes.
Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Drain.
Cook onion in drippings.
Add to corn mixture and simmer 5 minutes.
Add milk, sugar and salt; sprinkle with bacon.

title: cathy's russian tea
directions: Combine.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of tea.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar, beating thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour with cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture a small amount at a time, alternately with milk; add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Shape into a loaf. Place in loaf pan and cook at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Halfway through cooking time, cover in barbecue sauce and continue cooking until done.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 c. mix to 1 c. hot water.

title: cottage or ricotta cheese pie
directions: Cream together with a mixer the cheese and flour.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add sugar gradually, then lemon juice.
By hand, stir in milk.
Pour into pie shell and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Break egg into container or blender.
Add vinegar and dry ingredients.
Add 1/4 of the oil.
Cover; turn motor on low speed. Immediately uncover and pour in remaining oil, to a steady stream.
Turn motor up to high for last 5 seconds or so.

title: savory roast fresh ham
directions: Have butcher remove bones from ham.
Combine next 6 ingredients and rub half inside meat.
Combine remaining ingredients and distribute on inside of meat.
Tie securely together with cord.
Score fat and skin, them rub with remaining seasoning.
Put meat, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast in slow oven (325°) about 4 1/2 hours (30 minutes per pound).
If meat gets too brown, cover lightly with foil.

title: temptations
directions: Beat brown sugar and butter until fluffy.
Slowly beat in corn syrup, then egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt mixture.
Stir in the pecans and half of the sweet chocolate chunks.
Spread in an ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Cut in 2 1/2-inch squares.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: red chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken (save broth).
Saute onion and peppers in bacon grease.
Add tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and Texas Pete.
Let simmer.
Add ketchup and chicken broth.
Stir in peas, then add chicken pieces.
Serve over rice.

title: caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Generously grease
a
x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan; set
aside.
Blend	sugar,	corn syrup, Crisco and vanilla in large
saucepan.
Cook
on
medium
heat about 2 minutes or until light and foamy, stirring constantly. Remove from
heat; add popcorn,
tossing
to
coat.
Stir	in peanuts; spread in greased baking pan.
Bake
at
for	8 minutes. Use pancake turner to
push
popcorn
from bottom of pan; return to often for 7 minutes.
Cool
in pan;
break into bite size. Makes 2 quarts.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix butter, Karo, brown sugar and white sugar in saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil about 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Place on two greased cookie sheets and bake one hour at 200°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Then pour on waxed paper to cool.
May have to separate.

title: apple crisp #4
directions: Grease a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle over apples.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs and mincemeat.
Add flour and soup alternately.
Add nuts and fruit.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes (or until done) in a tube pan.

title: fast and fabulous fudge(microwave)
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with plastic wrap.
In a 3-quart microwavable bowl, combine Karo syrup and evaporated milk and stir until blended.
Microwave on High setting for 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in vanilla, confectioners sugar and nuts.
Blend together with spoon until thick and glossy. Spread into pan and refrigerate until firm (about 2 hours minimum).

title: royal chicken
directions: Arrange chicken breast halves in casserole dish (buttered). Top each breast with a slice of Swiss cheese.
Mix the 2 cans of cream of chicken soup with 1/2 can of water.
Pour this over chicken, then spread 2 cups crushed seasoned dressing mix over all and drizzle with 1/3 cup butter.
Bake, uncovered, 50 to 55 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hominy salad
directions: Rinse hominy and drain well.
Combine with remaining ingredients and drain well.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Mix together milk, butter, sugar and coconut. Cover with wax paper and chill for 24 hours. Melt chocolate with the shortening. Form coconut mixture into small patties and with a fork, dip into chocolate. Place onto wax paper to harden.

title: whole wheat carrot cake
directions: In a medium bowl, blend oil, sugar and brown sugar on low speed until mixed.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, blending well.
In separate bowl, stir together flour, salt, dry milk, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add to 4 egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts by hand.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube or 12-cup fluted tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until the cake tests done. Cool in pan; invert onto a serving plate.
Sprinkle sifted confectioners sugar on top.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: coffee brandy
directions: Dissolve and cool.
Measure and add equal amounts of vodka (a fifth).
Add one vanilla bean.
Bottle.
Let set 2 weeks.

title: party mints
directions: Combine butter, sugar and oil of peppermint.
Mix milk and food coloring and add to the butter-sugar mixture, mixing well with a hand beater.
Roll out in long 1/2-inch pieces.
Let each dry completely.

title: brazilian coffee
directions: Into each of 4 mugs, pour 1 cup coffee.
Microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes on High.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of cocoa mix and sugar for each cup.
Top with 2 tablespoons ice cream and a dash of cinnamon.

title: spice and applesauce cake
directions: Grease cake pan. Mix with spoon the cake mix, eggs, oil and pie filling. (Optional, 1 cup raisins and nuts.) Stir until well blended. Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate toffee nut squares
directions: Arrange a single layer of crackers (salty side up) in a jelly roll pan.
Melt together butter and brown sugar and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: summer snowball
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add milk.
Beat in flour and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in hot oil and brown.
When cool, shake in confectioners sugar.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Melt butter; cream in sugar and eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Dredge nuts and fruit in additional flour.
Add to mixture.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot cordial
directions: Mix well; cover tightly.
Stir first few days.
Wait 1 to 4 weeks before serving.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: In large container, melt margarine; stir in peanut butter. Add sugar and Rice Krispies.
By hand, shape into small logs. Refrigerate while melting chocolate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add sugar and mayonnaise and blend well. Add pineapple, cranberries and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Freeze.

title: turkey crunch
directions: Mix turkey with mushrooms, celery, onions, pimiento and put into casserole dish.
Blend
soup
and
milk and pour over turkey mixture.
Sprinkle
noodles
on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: yellow chiffon cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Mix oil, yolks, water and vanilla together.
Add to dry mixture; beat with spoon until smooth.
Put egg whites and cream of tartar in bowl. Beat until stiff.
Pour 2 mixtures together gradually folding gently until blended.
Bake in ungreased pan.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Line bottom of buttered 13 x 7-inch pan with crescent rolls.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bacon.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8. Good for breakfast or dinner.

title: applesauce date bars
directions: Cream the margarine, sugar and egg together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan, well-greased and floured, for 35 minutes or until tested.

title: quantity sausage cheese grits
directions: Cook, drain, crumble and set aside sausage.
In a large Dutch oven, stir grits in to boiling water.
Return them to a boil, then reduce heat.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Saute onion and margarine; add to grits to stir.
Add prepared sausage, chilies, pepper sauce, garlic salt and pimentos. Stir well.
Stir in eggs and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or in microwave until bubbly (10 to 15 minutes).
May be frozen before baking.
Serves 20.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar and add eggs, beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas.
Beat well after each addition.
Add nuts.
Pour in greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool.

title: chocolate cinnamon bars
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, 1 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Add butter or oleo, shortening, 1 egg and 1 egg yolk. Blend well and turn into a lightly greased jellyroll pan; spread evenly with spatula.
Beat egg white slightly; brush over mixture. Combine remaining 1/3 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, chocolate chips and walnuts; sprinkle over top.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: "karithopita" - walnut cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs for 20 minutes, then add a little soda, baking powder and flour, alternating with a little milk.
Mix slowly.
Keep adding until flour, soda and baking powder are all gone.
Add cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and orange rind, if used.
Mix well, then add chopped nuts.
Pour in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes; depends on your oven.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mince garlic.
Grate lemon peel.
Combine olive oil, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, lemon juice, minced garlic and grated lemon peel.
Shake very well.
Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and place in salad bowl.
Pour dressing over lettuce and sprinkle cheese.
Add croutons.
Toss salad.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and baking powder together; drop in 1 unbeaten egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Spread over sliced apples in a greased pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Melt Criso over apples. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cool cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion; place in large bowl.
Mix other ingredients; pour over onion and cucumbers.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: white chili
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into bite sized pieces.
Add to chicken stock mixture.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/4-inch thick.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Mix meal, flour and sugar and cover tomatoes.
Fry in oil or butter, about 1/4-inch, in frypan.
Cook 2 minutes on each side. Drain on paper towel.

title: lemon loaf
directions: Beat all ingredients for 7 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jelly roll(yields one roll)
directions: Beat egg yolks until almost thick; gradually beat 1/4 cup sugar into egg yolks.
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add 1/2 cup sugar to whites and beat very stiff.
Fold yolks into whites.
Add flour, salt and baking powder, sifted together.
Fold carefully.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes in a 10 1/2 x 15-inch pan, lined with wax paper.

title: pasta salad (with tomatoes)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Mixture should be moist.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and rinse well.
Combine the green beans, soups, milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Put 1/2 can onions over mixture. Bake in a 375° oven until brown on top.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well with mixer or in blender.
Pour into greased baking dish and cover with topping. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and eggs
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Brown pasta in butter until crispy and golden brown.
Beat eggs in bowl add salt and pepper to taste. Add beaten eggs to pasta, cook as you would scrambled eggs.
When eggs are cooked it's ready.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Blend first four ingredients and add salt.
Stir in 10 c. water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Add lemon juice and mix till right consistency.
Be sure your syrup is really thick.
Place in jars and water bath 20 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Blend eggs and cottage cheese. Add to muffin mix. Add oleo, onion and broccoli. Spray 9 x 13 inch pan with Pam. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat together the cream cheese and sugar.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze.
Take out 30 minutes before serving.
This salad can be kept in freezer up to 6 months.

title: banana-nut cake
directions: Heat oven
Put all ingredients in bowl.
With mixer, blend
all	1/2
minute
on
low speed and 3 minutes on high, scraping bowl constantly.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in tube or Bundt pan.
Can frost or dust with powdered sugar.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch flowerpot and silk flowers.

title: karo nut pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pie crust shell and bake at 350°.

title: hot chocolate float
directions: In a 2-cup container, microwave water, uncovered, on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until steaming hot. Stir in cocoa mix. Pour into a mug. Top hot chocolate with a small scoop of ice cream. Serve immediately.

title: yeast bread
directions: Sift 4 cups flour into an oversize crockery bowl.
Sift 4 cups flour into a smaller bowl, to which has been added 2 teaspoons baking powder, 2 teaspoons salt and 1 scant teaspoon soda.
Put milk in large saucepan; add sugar and Crisco.
Bring to a boil, but do not boil.
Remove from stove; place in sink with several inches of water to cool.
Place lid on top of pan.
Put yeast into warm water.
Dissolve.
When milk is cooled to lukewarm, add yeast; pour this into first bowl with only the flour.
Use rotary beater to distribute lumps.

title: miniature drop biscuits
directions: Cut butter into flour until crumbly.
Add sour cream.
Stir until mixture forms stiff dough.
Fill 2 x 1-inch muffin cups full.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Serve immediately.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar. Add eggs and juice from fruit cocktail. Mix soda and salt with flour. Add to first mixture. Add fruit cocktail last. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry fluff
directions: Prepare crust from graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cream cheese.
Mix Dream Whip as directed. Combine the two mixtures. Spread over crust. Refrigerate.
Spread cherry pie filling over top just before serving.

title: sugarless date-nut squares(diabetic)
directions: Simmer fruits in water for 5 minutes.
Stir in butter and margarine; cool mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients together. Stir in cooled fruit mixture.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool; cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 24 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Mix together cheeses, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper for filling.
Using a teaspoon, carefully fill cooked, cooled stuffing shells with the cheese mixture.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan, pour 1/2 of the sauce, then arrange the shells, open side up, in a single layer over the sauce.
Cover with remaining sauce and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Allow to stand, uncovered, for about 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings (about 36 shells).

title: chili rellenos
directions: Grate all cheese.
Split whole chilies and remove seeds.
In flat buttered baking dish, layer 1/2 chilies, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 chilies and 1/2 cheese.

title: roulade (beef birds)
directions: Slice roast thin.
Sprinkle each slice with salt and pepper. Roll onion and bacon in beef and hold together with toothpicks. In a Dutch oven or heavy covered pan, brown in bacon drippings on high or medium heat.
Cover meat with water and cook until tender, but firm.
Cool; pour flour mixture into broth and thicken gravy. Serve with noodles or spaetzle.

title: apple casserole
directions: Place apples in a casserole dish.
Mix rest of ingredients together; spread over apples.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice(easy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the uncooked rice on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then place salted chicken on rice.
Mix the remaining ingredients; bring to boil, then pour over chicken. Cook for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Saute onion and pepper in bacon fat.
Add okra, cut into 1-inch pieces and fry for 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Remove cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: orange poppy seed muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 1 1/2-quart mixing bowl, beat all ingredients at slow speed until moistened (about 1 minute).
Spoon batter into muffin tin lined with paper or sprayed with polyunsaturated cooking spray.
Bake 17 to 22 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 muffins.
Contains 134 calories per muffin, 3.3 g fat, 0 cholesterol and 50 g sodium.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix all together and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top.
Chill until very firm or freeze.
Cut into squares.
(Sometimes, I cut them first before freezing.)

title: delicious slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots (optional) and onion.
Combine all other ingredients and mix with vegetables.
Mix well.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all juices together in a punch bowl.
Add water and sugar to taste.
Add plenty of ice for dilution.
Add the bottle of ginger ale just before serving.
Serves about 50 people.

title: strawberry queen pie
directions: Heat water to boiling in 2-quart saucepan; remove from heat. Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup cold water (or ice water).
Cut ice cream into six pieces; add to hot liquid. Stir until melted.
Chill until mixture begins to thicken and mound when spooned, 20 to 25 minutes.
Fold in strawberries. Pour into cooled, baked pie shell.
Garnish with whipped cream and sliced strawberries if desired.
Chill 20 to 25 minutes or until firm.

title: ziti
directions: Cook noodles according to package instructions. Meanwhile, simmer tomato paste, 6 ounces of water, tomato sauce, margarine and seasonings.
Drain noodles.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Add almonds just before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crunch cake
directions: Spray Pam in 9 x 13-inch dish and pour in pie filling.
Slice fresh strawberries and add to filling (optional).
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Place pats of butter over mix.
Bake as directed on cake box.

title: munster hash
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower until tender.
Drain and place in ungreased baking dish.
Heat soups, milk and cheese until cheese melts.
Pour mixture over vegetables.
Gently stir once or twice.
Sprinkle with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: souped up potatoes
directions: Combine all of the preceding ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Chop maraschino cherries.
Mix with crushed pineapple, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook in saucepan until mixture is glossy.
(May need to add more cornstarch.)
Pour over yams in casserole and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: school no-bake chocolate cookies
directions: In saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir well. Drop onto wax paper.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: kraut-pork pinwheel
directions: Combine pork, bread crumbs, egg, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce; mix thoroughly.
On waxed paper, pat meat mixture to a 10 x 7-inch rectangle.
Combine sauerkraut and onion; spread evenly over meat.
Starting at narrow side, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Place loaf in shallow bake dish.
Arrange bacon slices across top.
Bake in oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars. Add eggs, vanilla and water. Add flour, soda and salt. Mix well. Add chips and nuts to mixture. Mix well. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Put ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Mix in the next 3 with a fork.
Divide dough into 5 balls and chill for 1/2 hour before rolling out.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream mayonnaise and cream cheese together.
Mix all ingredients together with cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop and brown together bacon and onion.
Add to beans and combine other ingredients, one at a time.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: four bean salad
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in small saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large container.
Pour sugar-vinegar mixture over beans and toss to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight to marinate.
Toss occasionally.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll in paprika and chill.
Makes 1 large ball or 2 small balls.

title: braised sirloin tips
directions: Brown meat in melted shortening.
Stir in consomme, wine or juice, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer covered one hour until meat is tender.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: diabetic chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine, egg, sweetener and vanilla. Stir in flour, baking soda and salt. Add chocolate chips and blend well. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 40 cookies.

title: crispy cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumbers and fill jug 1/2 full.
Add cloth bag filled with spices and finish adding the cucumbers.
Pour alum and salt on top and then add enough vinegar to cover the cucumbers.
Put lid on and let sit for 6 weeks.
Pour the vinegar off and remove the bag.
Pour cucumbers in large pan and cover with sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Return to jug and cover.
Store in a cool place. The older they get, the better they taste.
Keep a small container in the refrigerator if you like them cold.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add rest of ingredients and continue cooking.
Serve with taco chips, lettuce, sour cream and cheese.

title: dad's chili recipe
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Add kidney beans.
Slice tomatoes and add.
Add tomato paste and water to taste.
Add dry chili mix and Tabasco sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mediterranean open-faced sandwich
directions: Mix grated cheeses together with mayonnaise and minced onion. Add black olives and bacon, crumbled.
Spread mixture on pita breads (like a small pizza) and broil 2 to 3 minutes until cheese is bubbly and just slightly brown.
Should make enough for 6 to 8 pita sandwiches
or 3 to 4 large pita breads.
Delicious!
