title: classic green bean casserole(cooking time:  30 minutes)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Stir in green beans and 1/2 can of onions.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: the ultimate grilled cheese
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth.
Stir in cheeses, garlic powder, salt and bacon.
Spread the mixture on a slice of bread (about 1/3 cup).
Top with another slice of bread.
Butter the outsides of the bread and grill.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Combine spinach, onion, water in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Drain well and squeeze to remove excess liquid.
Combine spinach mixture and remaining ingredients in medium size mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets.
Chill at least 30 minutes before baking. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Put chicken pieces, onion and cheese in each tortilla and roll; place in baking dish, seam side down.
Heat soups, milk and chilies thoroughly and pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with cheese and onion and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lefsa
directions: Boil the cream, water and lard together and pour over the flour.
Add a dash of salt.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix all except candy and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 X 9 X 2 pan.
Sprinkle nuts and candy over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: granola breakfast bar(weight watchers)
directions: Mix and shape into bar.
Wrap and freeze.

title: caramel-pecan cheesecake
directions: Toast butter, coconut and pecans in a skillet and let cool. In another bowl mix the cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Layer ingredients as follows:
1/4 cream cheese mixture, 1/4 jar caramel topping and 1/4 toasted coconut and nuts. Repeat layers.
Place in freezer and serve slightly thawed.
Very rich!!

title: fluffy pudding frosting
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix and sugar.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended.
Stir in whipped topping gently.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes about 5 cups or enough for two 9-inch layers.

title: brown soda bread
directions: Oven temperature should be 375°, reduced to 350°.
Preheat oven.
Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Combine well the fingers.
In another bowl, mix the eggs with the yogurt and water.
Make a well in the dry mixture and slowly pour on the yogurt and water.
Mix with your hands until you get a nice soft dough, not too wet.
A dough that is too wet or too stiff will result in a hard, heavy bread.
Lightly flour a worktop or pastry board.
Divide the dough in half.
Make 2 flat rounds of bread on the board.
Cut a deep cross in the middle of each loaf.
Place in the preheated oven for 10 minutes, then reduce the heat.
Bake until the bottom of the bread sounds hollow when knocked.
This takes about 30 minutes.

title: good fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding and fruit, then fold in Cool Whip.

title: chile verde
directions: Put a little oil in a large skillet and brown meat.
Remove from pan and set aside.
Saute peppers, onions and garlic in same skillet.
In saucepan, heat tomatoes and water to a simmer. Combine all ingredients in skillet and simmer covered for 2 hours. Uncover and simmer another 45 minutes until done.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain.
Mix soup, eggs and hash browns together.
Ad meat.
Top with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 2-quart casserole.

title: company coming breakfast
directions: Brown sausage or bacon first; drain.
Line greased 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Sprinkle cheese, ham and mushrooms.
Mix together eggs and milk.
Slowly pour over ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Chopped onion and/or green pepper is optional.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks until light in color.
Add sugar and beat again.
Stir in milk and rum. Chill 2 to 3 hours. Whip the cream, then fold into chilled mixture. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 20 servings.

title: house slaw
directions: In pan, combine mustard, sugar, celery seed, salt, white vinegar and salad oil.
Bring to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture.
Chill 4 hours.

title: fresh fried corn
directions: Combine corn, milk, egg yolk, salt, butter, vanilla and sugar in medium mixing bowl; stir well. Beat egg white until stiff but not dry; fold into corn mixture. Spoon into nonstick 8- inch square baking disk, and bake at 350 degree for 30 to 40 minutes or until set. Serve and enjoy.

title: honey carrots
directions: Wash and trim carrots.
Cook in small amount of boiling salted water for 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Melt margarine in a skillet or saucepan.
Add sugar, honey and carrots.
Cook over low heat, turning carrots frequently until each is well glazed. Sprinkle with chopped parsley or mint and serve immediately.

title: best oven dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly mix first 8 ingredients.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Mix bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot. Serves 4.

title: potato burgers
directions: Mix potatoes, onion, carrot and beef.
Make into large patties. Roll into flour.
Brown on both sides in skillet over medium heat. Dilute mushroom soup.
Pour over patties.
Cover with a lid and simmer for 1 hour.

title: good apple pie
directions: Put apples in a casserole dish. Sift flour and sugar together. Add egg.
Mix until it crumbles like cornmeal.
Put over apples in pan.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top and bake slow.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix together margarine, soup, onions, sour cream and cheese and pour over potatoes.
Mix everything slightly. Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put 1/2 batter in tube pan.
Mix 3 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/2 nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Then put other half of batter in.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; cool and peel. Mash potatoes and add sugar, milk, eggs and margarine. Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and dash of nutmeg. Pour into baking dish; cover with marshmallows. Place in oven at 325° and brown lightly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes.
Mix all together with mixer.
Pour into baking dish.

title: goulash
directions: Brown beef and pork.
When cooked, pour off excess grease.. Add onion, peppers, drained noodles, corn, rice and soup.
Beat eggs and add cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
If dry, add milk and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cauliflower should be put in cold salted water, head down, for 30 minutes.
Then drop into boiling salted water, heat up, and cook until tender.
Cauliflower should be cooked uncovered and rapidly.
Do not overcook.
Drain and serve as desired.
Good served with heated Cheez Whiz poured over it.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients; mix in next 5 ingredients.
Add chocolate chips and Hershey bar.
Make large cookies and bake at 375° for 7 minutes.
Add walnuts if desired.

title: cream cheese topping
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk. Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in whipped topping. Serve atop anything you think needs a pick-up.
Yields 2 or more cups.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Wipe 3 pounds of beef with damp cloth.
Rub with garlic, salt and pepper.
Place in crock.
Heat, but do not boil, vinegar or white wine with equal part of water, onion, bay leaves, peppercorns and sugar.
Pour mixture while hot over the beef so it is more than half covered.
Place lid over crock and put in refrigerator.
Leave meat in refrigerator for 4 days, turning once a day.
Drain, saving the vinegar, and cook meat until tender. Remove from pot and replace where it will remain hot.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Blend with flour.
Stir with wire whisk.
Add box of gingersnaps to thicken gravy.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Take each chicken breast; flatten and top with dried beef. Roll, then wrap with a strip of bacon; secure with a toothpick. Arrange bundles in a Pyrex pan.
Combine undiluted mushroom soup and sour cream; pour over breasts.
Bake for 3 hours at 300°.
If the breasts are browning too rapidly, put loose foil on top for last part of cooking.
Can be easily adapted to serve a large crowd.

title: four bean salad
directions: Drain
all
beans and corn;
wash off red kidney beans. Place beans and corn in a large container with a lid.
Mix the vinegar, sugar,
oil,
onion
and pepper; pour over beans and corn.
Best if made 24 hours before serving.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk; stir to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto well floured board with floured hands; pat down to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into strips with slit in middle.
Fry in deep fryer until golden brown on both sides.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and few grains of salt.
Stir milk in gradually.
Place in double boiler.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and coats spoon.
Then cool and add vanilla.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Cream
together with mixer the cream cheese and butter. Add 1 box confectioners sugar and mix well. Add the second box of confectioners
sugar
and
1/4 cup warm water and mix well. Add the
melted
German
chocolate. Take out 2 1/2 cups of the mixture and
reserve
it
for
frosting. Add to the remaining mixture the shortening and eggs (one at a time) and mix well.

title: mae mae's fruit cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs to sugar mixture.
Cut soda into flour.
Mix flour and soda with pecans, dates, pineapple and cherries.
Mix all ingredients well.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve dip warm in fondue.

title: cucumber kim chee
directions: Peel cucumbers and rub with salt under running water.
Slice cucumbers into thin slices and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons salt. Mix well and place in refrigerator overnight.
Strain cucumbers under running water.
Be sure to rinse all salt off.
Dry cucumber slices with paper towels.
Chop green onions and garlic finely and mix with cucumbers.
Mix 1 tablespoon ground red pepper with a small amount of boiling water.
Add to cucumber mixture.
Add 1 tablespoon sugar; mix well.
Kim Chee is ready to eat.
This dish can also be prepared using cabbage.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut together and spread on bottom of greased 9 x 13 pan.
Mix up cake mix according to directions on box, then pour over nuts and coconut mixture.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and margarine together and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients.

title: summertime smoothies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in blender; liquefy until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Pour into tall glasses.
Garnish with fresh strawberry.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple cole slaw
directions: Grate or chop cabbage fine.
Add undrained pineapple and mix. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and salt. Add to cabbage and mix well.
Refrigerate for at least one hour before serving.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 2-crust, 9-inch pie.
Combine all ingredients.
Fill pie shell.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon lemon juice; dot with 1 tablespoon butter.
Adjust top crust, cutting slits on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: apple cider
directions: Put spices in top of a coffee pot.
Heat.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tortillas.
Let set for an hour before spreading on tortillas.
Roll up tightly in jelly roll fashion.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice and serve.
To soften tortillas, place over burner on low.
Keep turning until soft. Spread filling; be sure to spread filling on edge of tortillas. When refrigerating rolls, cover well or place in a covered container.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini.
Rinse until cool.
Chop onions, tomatoes, mushrooms and green peppers.
Slice olives in half.
Break broccoli into small pieces.
Combine ingredients with Italian seasoning and dressing.
Marinate overnight.

title: easy oven roast
directions: Take
roast and sprinkle with salts and pepper.
Rub in garlic powder to taste.
Brown in skillet on both sides.
Peel potatoes and
split	in
half.
Peel carrots, cut in half and split lengthwise.
Peel
onions
and
slice.
Cut celery into small pieces.
Prepare oven bag as directed on package.
Place part of all

vegetables in large oven cooking bag, then put in roast; add more vegetables to side of roast, then add remaining vegetables. Be sure that some of the onion and celery are on top of roast. Cook at 325° until tender and brown.

title: a & m strawberry dessert
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown and crumbly.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hank's fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, salt and evaporated milk together.
Stir constantly.
Bring to rolling boil.
Time for 12 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Add Marshmallow Fluff and vanilla.
Mix well.
Work quickly.
Add walnuts, if desired.
Spread into lightly buttered large cookie sheet.
Makes 5 pounds.
Can use peanut butter chips
or butterscotch chips in place of chocolate.

title: pork ribs and sauerkraut
directions: In a 3 1/2-quart saucepan, heat oil and brown ribs.
Turn burner to low-medium heat.
Layer potatoes, sauerkraut and onion. Continue layers until finished. Garnish with scallion.
Salt and pepper. Cover and cook for 2 to 3 hours until pork is tender.

title: apple crapple cake
directions: Beat the eggs and sugar well (5 minutes); add oil.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients; mix.
Mix with a spoon.
Stir in the apples and nuts.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, milk and oil together.
Sift flour and salt over the egg mixture and beat until smooth.
Fill 6 popover cups 3/4 full.
Bake 30 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 15 minutes.
Makes 6.

title: zucchini ripiene(stuffed squash)
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Scoop out inside.
Chop up insides and fry insides in oil with parsley, onion, garlic, ground beef and seasonings until browned.
Cool.

title: sugar snap peas
directions: Put water, sugar and margarine in frypan.
Add peas, fresh or 1 package frozen, then turn on heat under pan.
Stir frequently and gently until peas are heated and coated with margarine.
Do not overcook.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, half bell pepper, half onion, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons of chili powder.
Shape into patties and cook in small amount of oil until brown on both sides.
While patties are browning, in a saucepan melt tomato paste, tomato sauce, 4 cans of water, rest of bell pepper, onion and 1 to 1 1/2 tablespoons of chili powder.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a low boil.
Drain grease from patties and pour tomato mixture over patties.
Cook at medium boil for about 1 hour.

title: eggnog punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered, 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add whipped cream.
Pour into Oreo cookie pie crust.
Sprinkle with Oreo cookie crumbs.
Freeze and serve.

title: cinnamon bran pancakes
directions: Mix milk, egg and oil in bowl.
Add sifted dry ingredients and thoroughly mix.
Cook on preheated skillet.
Top with fresh fruit, warmed jam or maple syrup.
These are so good, no one needs to know they are also very healthy.

title: dutch bean salad
directions: Drain beans of juices.
Place in a bowl and mix.
Slice green pepper and onion.
Add to mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients into a small pot and heat over low heat.
Allow sugar to melt.
Remove from heat.
Let cool.
When cool, pour over bean salad.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill in refrigerator for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve.

title: pistachio fluff
directions: Blend together the sour cream and pudding (do not use Mixmaster).
Add undrained pineapple and 1 can of drained mandarin oranges.
Add mini marshmallows.
Place in bowl and garnish with the remaining oranges and the cherries.
Refrigerate several hours and serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Shape into balls, then place in a glass baking dish.
Mix together catsup, grape jelly and lemon juice; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together with a fork.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie plate. Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour (exactly).

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour. Drain.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mama's chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts or whole chicken.
Cover bottom of large baking dish with 1/2 box crushed Escort crackers.
Mix in bowl, mushroom or celery soup, sour cream, chicken broth from chicken and small pieces of chicken.
Mix well.
Pour over crackers. Crumble rest of crackers on top.
Top with pats of butter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, slice in 1/4-inch slices, dip in bread crumbs, then in egg mixture and again in crumbs.
Fry in oil until brown. Saute the onion and bell pepper in same skillet eggplant was fried in until soft.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook until blended.
Place eggplant in casserole dish in alternating layers with cheese and sauce.
On top, layer cheese and sauce.
Bake covered for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove cover and bake until crust is brown.
(Ground meat can be added to make a meat casserole.)

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the chocolate chips for 2 minutes. Add chips.
Pour into greased (use Pam) Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodle marzetti
directions: In skillet, brown hamburger, onion and soy sauce.
Remove fat; add green pepper, garlic powder, tomatoes and bouillon cubes. Simmer for 5 minutes.
In a small bowl, blend cornstarch, water and sugar; add to mixture in skillet.
Cook and stir for 5 more minutes.

title: dumplins or drop biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together with a fork. Then add milk and oil. Stir with a fork until it makes a ball in the bowl. For biscuits, spoon drop on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 450 for 10-14 minutes.

title: peach blueberry pie
directions: Stir together flour and salt.
Cut Crisco into above mixture with pastry blender.
Add ice water and blend.
Roll dough out between sheets of wax paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in chopped nuts and refrigerate.
Makes two small or one large cheese ball.
Can be frozen.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix together flour, soda and salt.
Pour water over whole bran cereal.
Set aside.

title: condensed tomato soup
directions: Simmer tomatoes and chicken broth for 30 minutes.
Add the whipping cream or half & half until it's a pretty pink.
Serve in a bowl.
You may want to add 1 - 2 tsp. sugar.

title: baked pork chops with dressing
directions: Season chops and brown in 1 tbl. oil. Remove from skillet. Place in 13x9x2-inch baking dish. Saute onion in melted butter till tender, not brown. Add bread cubes, poultry seasoning, celery salt, and 1/4 cup water. Mix lightly. Shape dressing in mounds on top of pork chops. Coat potatoes with oil and place around the pork chops.

title: old time beef stew
directions: Brown meat, then add water and vegetables.
Cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes or until all is tender at checking.
Combine the water and flour to make paste.
Add to the stew to thicken juices. Yields 9 cups.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Melt butter and cheese together in pan.
Put broccoli and rice, uncooked, in dish.
Add chestnuts.
Mix in cheese and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Place rolls in glass casserole dish and press up against the sides.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.
Brown beef.
Add taco mix and tomato sauce.
Layer meat and then cheese until used up.
Place in oven and cook until cheese is melted (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Cut when cool.
Sprinkle lettuce, tomatoes and salsa on top.

title: spiced canned peaches
directions: Bring peach juice, sugar, vinegar, spices and cinnamon stick to rapid boil.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add peaches and return to a boil.
Set off heat and leave until cool.
Can store in refrigerator until gone.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: *For fresh apples, use 6 cups peeled, cored and sliced plus 1 cup of water.
Cook fruit down for several minutes.

title: pineapple-orange cake
directions: Beat for 2 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.

title: caramel fudge brownies
directions: While brownies are baking, mix in small saucepan over low heat 20 caramels with milk.
Stir until smooth and caramels are melted.
Immediately after removing brownies from oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Drizzle with caramel.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine celery, onion, potatoes, chicken bouillon cubes and water.
Cook over moderate heat for 20 minutes. Add frozen vegetables and cook until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and cheese, heat well, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.

title: punch
directions: Freeze ice ring ahead; orange slices and cherries may be added to water before freezing.
Just before serving, place ice ring in punch bowl.
Add the rest of the ingredients that have been mixed together.

title: french veal stew
directions: Heat 3 tablespoons butter and fry meat (do not brown).
Remove meat.
Fry onions 5 minutes.
Remove.
Melt remaining butter with meat juices.
Add flour and cook gently 3 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add broth.
Bring to boil, stirring.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add veal, carrots and onions.
Cook and cover on low heat for 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cream, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Reheat without boiling.

title: peppermint pears
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, water and lemon juice. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Peel pears, leaving stems attached.
Cut base of each pear so that pear sits level. Using a small, pointed knife, carefully scoop out seeds from base, so pear remains whole.

title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients first, then add water as suitable to taste.

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange cooked vegetables in a 12 x 8-inch (2-quart) baking dish.
In medium saucepan, melt margarine.
Add mushrooms; saute over medium heat until tender.
Stir in flour, bouillon, onion powder, pepper and half and half; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add cheese. Stir until melted.
Pour evenly over vegetables; gently toss vegetables to coat.
Sprinkle evenly with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom of muffin cups.
Beat egg with fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened, batter should be lumpy.
Fold in 1 cup well drained blueberries or 3/4 cup canned.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and butter in bowl; pat firmly into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test to see when it is done.

title: frozen salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together, folding it in thoroughly.
Mix on low speed for 2 minutes.
It should form a high peak.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in butter; add onion and garlic and brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: mama's pot roast
directions: Mix garlic powder (or salt), celery salt, table salt and black pepper.
Rub mixture on roast.
Sprinkle with flour, brown on all sides in a little oil--be sure meat is a good dark brown. Add water to cover roast in pan and coffee.
Bring to boil, turn heat down
to slow boil.
Add chopped onion.
Cook approximately 4 to 5 hours slowly till meat is fork tender.
Add vegetables and continue to cook till veggies are done.

Remove roast and veggies to platter-slice roast against grain of meat.Make a gravy by mixing flour with a little water, then adding to broth in pan where roast cooked. Any leftover roast and veggies, put into gravy, add a can of tomatoes and mixed vegetables and have a great soup next day.

title: praline chip cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Beat butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in a large bowl with electric mixer until well blended. With mixer on low speed, gradually add flour mixture.
Beat just until blended.
Stir in pecans and chips.

title: balloon blobs
directions: Blow up a balloon and keep it inflated for at least 1 minute. Do not tie a knot in the end.
After 1 minute, let all the air out. Fit a funnel into the open end of the balloon.
Carefully spoon flour into the funnel, tapping and shaking the funnel to get the flour into the balloon.
Put as much flour in the balloon as you can.
Remove the funnel.
Tie a knot in the end of the balloon. Wash and dry the Balloon Blob.
Draw a face or design on the blob if you like.
Push, pull and stretch it into different shapes.

title: baked fish and cream
directions: Place fish and cream in shallow individual baking dish. Dot with butter. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake in a hot oven (400°) for 10 minutes. Serves 1.

title: mrs. field's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix flour, oatmeal, salt, baking soda and powder.
Mix all ingredients and add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and pecans.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan on stove top.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk and heat until mixture starts to boil.
Remove from heat and mix in vanilla, a dash of salt and peanut butter.
Stir in oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: peach cobbler pie
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in pan.
Mix flour, milk and 1 cup sugar and pour evenly over margarine.
Heat 4 to 5 cups sliced peaches with 1 cup sugar (6 cups peaches to 1 1/4 cups sugar) until heated.
Spoon over crust. Bake for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients; then add vanilla, nuts, eggs, oil and sugar.
Mix and beat real good.
Mix eggs, oil and sugar together before adding to the first 7 ingredients.
Then add zucchini and raisins.
Grease and flour pan; cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes and onions in a pot with enough water to cover them.
Add salt to taste.
Cook until fork goes in them.

title: enchiladas excelente(325 calories and 7 grams fat per serving)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In nonstick skillet, cook turkey until no longer pink, breaking into small pieces with spoon.
Add 3/4 cup of Pace picante sauce, beans, bell pepper and seasonings.
Cook and stir until most of liquid has evaporated, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in onions.
Spoon 1/3 cup mixture onto each tortilla; roll up and place seam down in 13 x 19-inch glass baking dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Spoon remaining 1 1/4 cups Pace picante sauce over enchiladas.
Bake 15 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with cheese; return to oven for 2 minutes.
Top as desired; serve with additional Pace picante sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Combine soups and Minute rice.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup mix over all.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours. Do not peek.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with cornbread stuffing mix, cornflake crumbs or bread crumbs; bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Melt the butterscotch chips and stir in the peanut butter. Add the marshmallows and the chow mein noodles.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce and water; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: homemade salsa
directions: Mix together oil and vinegar.
Combine other ingredients and mix with oil mixture.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours and serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and mix with mixer until smooth.
Add oats and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet or wax paper.

title: easy broccoli bake
directions: Combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
In 10 x 6-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of the broccoli, 1/2 the soup mixture and 1/2 can of the onions.
Top with remaining broccoli and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions; bake 5 minutes.
Or cover with wax paper and microwave on High 8 minutes, rotating dish halfway through heating.
Top with remaining onions.
Microwave, uncovered, 1 minute.
Makes 6 servings.

title: whole pickles or christmas pickles
directions: Put cucumbers and other ingredients in a gallon jar.
Add enough water to completely cover cucumbers and seal jar.
After three months, slice cucumbers into thin slices and drain.
Layer with 5 to 6 cups of sugar and let stand overnight.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs one at a time until frothy.
Gradually add sugar and continue to beat until sugar is incorporated.
Heat milk and butter but do not boil.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Alternate adding the flour mixture and milk mixture into the egg mixture, but do not beat.
Stir in the vanilla.

title: mexican mix casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty can of chili into casserole dish. Add drained corn and grated cheese.
Crumble chips over top of casserole and press down.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Serve with extra chips.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Let stand in sugar.
Sift flour; add soda, cinnamon and salt.
Resift.
Add oil, eggs and vanilla to apples.
Add dry mix.
Mix in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: quick & easy clam chowder
directions: Saute Onion in Butter, add Clam's broth from the canned clams, Water, and Potatoes.
Cook until tender.
Add Clams, Milk, Salt, Pepper.
Heat through.

title: violet jelly
directions: Gather a fully-packed quart of dry, open violet blossoms. Pour boiling water over them and let sit overnight.
Strain out the flowers.
Add juice of 1 lemon and sugar (more sugar may be added, if desired).
Bring to a boil; add pectin.
Return to a full boil and boil hard about 3 minutes.
Skim foam, pour into jars and seal.

title: cilantro corn salad
directions: MIX salad dressing, yogurt, cilantro and ground ginger.
ADD corn, red pepper and jalapeno pepper; cover. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: best bread pudding
directions: Put bread crumbs in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat milk with butter, stirring until the butter melts. Pour over bread crumbs.
Stir in sugar, eggs, salt, cinnamon, raisins and vanilla.
Place baking dish in a large deep pan.
Add 1 inch of water to the larger pan.

title: florida barbecued ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs and parboil for 2 hours.
Combine barbecue ingredients and brush both sides of the ribs.
Cook 5-inches from coals 8 minutes each side, brushing with sauce and turning ribs constantly.
Heat remaining sauce and serve with ribs.

title: cranberry-cherry punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in a large bowl.
Add lemonade concentrate and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cranberry juice cocktail.
It can be frozen at this point. Remove from freezer about 3 to 4 hours before serving and add ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: troy's impossible vegetable pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a bowl and then put in a greased casserole dish.
Place the following 5 ingredients in a blender and mix for 1 minute.
Pour this mixture over vegetables in the casserole dish.
Do not cover.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: In butter, fry onion and celery.
In a blender, put water, cooked pumpkin, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into crock-pot; add fried mixture.
Chop potatoes, carrots and broccoli.
Add soup and chicken broth.
Cook on high for 3 hours.
Cut top off medium size pumpkin; clean out seeds and fibers.
Serve soup in the pumpkin.

title: taco dinner
directions: Cook meat lightly in skillet; remove excess grease.
Add taco mix, tomato sauce and water.
Mix well.
Add can refried beans. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Add tortilla chips.
Pour into a casserole dish; bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cover top with Cheddar cheese the last 5 minutes of cooking time if desired.

title: orange balls
directions: Roll vanilla wafers until fine.
Blend in soft margarine and work in orange juice, sugar and nuts.
Chill for 1 hour, then form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: one-step lasagne
directions: Can also add, if desired, 1 small can mushroom pieces, drained.

title: touchdown taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans in a baking dish. In a bowl, combine sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Finely chop garlic and add to mixture. Spread evenly over bean mixture. Grate cheese over top and bake 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: shanghi chicken
directions: Chop chicken; saute until firm.
Add celery; cook 1/2 minute. Add sprouts, sliced water chestnuts, soy sauce and pepper and cook 1 minute.
Add onion; spoon over rice and serve with noodles.

title: nut bread with honey glaze
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Blend molasses with buttermilk; stir into dry ingredients.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
When baked, mix honey and butter.
Pour on top and sprinkle with some crushed pecans.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: oriental chicken with vegetables
directions: In medium skillet, heat oil and cook chicken until almost done.
Remove.
Add vegetables, the soup mix blended with water, soy sauce, garlic powder and ginger.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring occasionally, five minutes or until sauce thickens.
Add chicken and red pepper.
Serve over hot rice.
tags: cream of chicken flavor soup mix

title: onion lovers twist
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
(Do not use Pam, as bread will burn on bottom.)
In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, water, milk, butter and egg.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to form soft dough.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in size, 45 to 60 minutes.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup
and	add
gelatine.	Add rest of ingredients and mix in
blender.
Grease mold (Tupperware is the best kind to use for this) with oil.
Don't put in hot water to loosen.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet with onion.
Add mushroom soup, sour cream and dill weed.
Cook until well done.
Add to noodles.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cucumbers, onions and green peppers.
Add a handful of canning salt.
Set overnight at room temperature.
Drain well. Place in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients, placing whole cloves in a small cloth and tie the opening off.
(A bread closure works well).
Cook 30 minutes just at the simmer point.
Remove the cloth containing the whole cloves and can in hot, sterilized jars.
If jars, lids and relish are all boiling hot there is no need to process in a canner or pressure canner.

title: marinated nibbler salad
directions: Cook corn according to package directions.
Cut in half to form 12 pieces.
Combine cooked corn, cooked rigatoni, tomatoes, zucchini and olives in large bowl.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: icebox cake
directions: Set graham crackers aside.
Whip whipping cream and add Hershey's chocolate to taste.
Alternate whipping cream and a pack of graham crackers in layers, compressing lightly to form a cake. Repeat until box of crackers is gone.
Frost with rest of whipped cream.
Place in refrigerator for 2 to 4 hours to set.
Cut and serve like a cake.

title: squash and apple casserole
directions: Peel squash and cut in cubes.
Add apple slices.
Melt margarine, sugar and spices. Add flour to thicken slightly, stirring constantly.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together butter, sugar, peanut butter and vanilla.
Make into balls.
Refrigerate.
Dip 1/2 way into chocolate chips and paraffin which have been melted together in a double boiler. Place on wax paper for chocolate to harden.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tins with liners.
Press crumbs with shot glass. Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix well.
Fill muffin pans 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from pan when cool. Chill.
Top with fruit, jam or powdered sugar.

title: prepared horseradish sauce
directions: Make a cream sauce of butter, flour and milk; add horseradish, mustard, salt and pepper.

title: apple cornbread
directions: Combine sifted dry ingredients. Add milk and egg; stir until smooth. Add melted shortening and apple. Bake in a shallow, greased pan for 20 minutes at 375°. Cut into squares to serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Add onion.
Put in boiler; cover with water.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 30 minutes on medium.
Add soup; reduce heat to low and continue to cook 15 to 20 minutes.
You may need to add a small amount of water.
(You can also add a can of cheese broccoli soup.)

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry
ingredients and onion; set aside.
Just before cooking, add egg and milk, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil.
Fry for 3 to 4 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: borden's low-fat cherry pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Top with cherry pie filling when serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: black bottom banana bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Blend in bananas.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Divide batter in half.
Add cocoa in half.
Spread the cocoa mixture in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon on remaining batter and swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Yield: 2 1/2 to 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Cook in a double
boiler
marshmallows
and 1/2 cup milk. Cool.
Chip the square of chocolate.
Whip the whipping cream
and fold in the marshmallows.	Add the chocolate. Fill the pie shell and cool for 2 hours or more.

title: cheesy beef pie
directions: Saute beef, green pepper and onion in a skillet until meat is done.
Drain well.
Return to skillet.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg.
Mix well and stir into meat mixture.
Spoon into 8-inch baking dish.
Split biscuits and place on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meaty spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet with onions and green pepper; break up beef with a fork.
Drain and put ground beef into crock-pot.
Add all other ingredients and cook on low for several hours (or while at work!).
Makes approximately enough sauce to serve over spaghetti for 8.
May be frozen in various serving sizes in Ziploc storage bags or plastic containers suitable for freezing.
Stores well.
Tastes better the second day.
Thaw and reheat to serve over variety of different pastas.
Recipe can be varied using Italian sausage or mixing sliced pepperoni with the ground beef.

title: spaghetti with haddock
directions: Cut and measure all ingredients before starting to cook.
Do not separate haddock fillets.
Cut each block of haddock into 3 pieces; set aside.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet or electric frying pan over medium heat (300°) 5 minutes or until hot.
Add mushrooms and garlic; saute 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Combine mushroom soup, milk and 1 cup of the Parmesan cheese in skillet.
Stir until blended.
Add spaghetti and parsley. Toss until coated.
Arrange fish on top.
Combine mushrooms and spinach.
Arrange on top of fish.
Cover and cook over low heat (220°) 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, cover and simmer 10 minutes more or until fish flakes with fork.
Makes 6 servings.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Line square pan with foil.
In heavy saucepan melt chips with condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat and stir in walnuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Remove from pan.
Place on cutting board.
Peel off foil; cut into squares.

title: garden bake
directions: Break cauliflower into small pieces.
Cook cauliflower with celery, uncovered, in boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain, reserving 3/4 cup liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Add flour; blend.
Gradually add milk and reserved liquid.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add green pepper.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Place in buttered 10 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: gooey bars
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix the first four ingredients and press into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Cream the last four ingredients and pour over the cake mix.
Bake for 35 minutes.
